ntil smooth. Cut off both ends of each of the yellow squash. Spiralize the squash with Blade B, and chop the noodles several times so that they are easier to eat. Be sure to slice the part of the squash that is not spiralized and mix them with the noodles. NOTE: If you do not own a spiralizer, use a vegetable peeler to create yellow squash ribbons. If you are adding fennel to this dish, heat a tablespoon of oil in a small saut pan over medium-high heat. When the pan is hot, add the fennel and saut them for about 4-5 minutes or until they turn translucent. Season with some fresh dill and salt. In a large bowl, mix the noodles and sauce together. Serve with the fennel and plum tomatoes. Refrigerate any leftovers in an airtight container.', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/PTQSXRCL/yellow-squash-noodles-with-tomato-basil-sauce', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10211641', 'name': 'squash noodles', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Yellow Squash Noodles'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 1/2 Tbs olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10211529', 'name': 'roma tomatoes', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '5 medium roma tomatoes, halved and seeded'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '4 cloves garlic, peeled'}, {'iid': 's_11955', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 sun-dried tomatoes (I used the kind that is not packed in oil)'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil leaves', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup fresh basil leaves, loosely packed'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of sea salt'}, {'iid': 's_10211641', 'name': 'squash', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '3 large yellow squash'}, {'iid': 's_10411529', 'name': 'plum tomatoes', 'qty': 0.6666667, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '2/3 cup yellow plum tomatoes (optional)'}, {'iid': 's_11957', 'name': 'sautéed fennel', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Sautéed Fennel (Optional)'}, {'iid': 's_11957', 'name': 'fennel bulb', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 fennel bulb, thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_2045', 'name': 'dill', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs fresh dill, chopped'}]}, {'rid': 's_649926', 'title': 'Lentil Rice Soup', 'inst': 'Place lentils in a saucepan and cover with water; soak for a few hours or overnight. Drain and add all ingredients except rice. Cook over low heat, covered, about 1 hour, or till lentils are soft. After 1 hour, add brown rice. Cook longer, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. With a wooden spoon, crush some of the cooked lentils to thicken soup. Remove bay leaf and cloves before serving.', 'serv': 10, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TTYRBZGX/lentil-rice-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaf', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large bay leaf'}, {'iid': 's_20040', 'name': 'brown rice', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup brown rice'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 carrot chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10111143', 'name': 'celery stalk', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 celery stalk chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10416069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '1 lb dried lentils'}, {'iid': 's_1002041', 'name': 'tarragon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon dried tarragon'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium onion , chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon pepper'}, {'iid': 's_99253', 'name': 'vegetable salt', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Vegetable salt to taste'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable stock', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups vegetable stock or canned broth'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '8 cups cold water'}]}, {'rid': 's_653682', 'title': 'One Pot Veggie Quinoa', 'inst': 'Heat oil in a wok/skillet/nonstick saucepan. Add all the herbs including garlic in the warm oil. Immediately add onions to it and saut until golden brown. Add green pepper, broccoli, cauliflower and cover and cook for few minutes. The veggies should be slightly soft but crunchy. Add crinkled carrots and saut for 1 minute. Add tomatoes and again cover and cook for few minutes, until the tomatoes release its juice. Add burrata cheese to get the creamy texture. Cover and cook again for 2 minutes. Add salt, ketchup and quinoa. Saut until quinoa is well coated. Add water, cover and cook until water is absorbed and quinoa is well cooked. This may take about 10-15 minutes. Garnish with more crushed pepper if required and serve hot.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/RD2F8BLT/one-pot-veggie-quinoa', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011090', 'name': 'broccoli florets', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup broccoli florets'}, {'iid': 's_93617', 'name': 'burrata', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup burrata'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'crinkled carrots', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup crinkled carrots'}, {'iid': 's_10011135', 'name': 'cauliflower florets', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup cauliflower florets'}, {'iid': 's_2003', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp dried basil'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '3 cloves of garlic, minced, or chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11333', 'name': 'peppers', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup green peppers (chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_11935', 'name': 'ketchup', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp ketchup'}, {'iid': 's