', 'name': 'seasoning', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon Italian seasoning'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 16.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '16 boiling onions, cut the ends and remove the outside layer'}, {'iid': 's_1038', 'name': 'romano cheese', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup Romano cheese, shredded'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.125, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/8 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_10211641', 'name': 'squash', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 yellow squash, sliced'}]}, {'rid': 's_633120', 'title': 'Avocado and Cannellini Bean Salad', 'inst': 'Throw all of the ingredients together in a container. Measure out the dressing and place in a plastic baggie. When ready to eat pour in the dressing, shake and enjoy!', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/7W6PWGLX/avocado-and-cannellini-bean-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium avocado, mashed to a paste'}, {'iid': 's_10111251', 'name': 'baby spinach', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup romaine lettuce or baby spinach, shredded'}, {'iid': 's_99249', 'name': 'balsamic vinaigrette', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon Low Fat Balsamic Vinaigrette'}, {'iid': 's_10716050', 'name': 'cannellini beans', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup cannellini beans'}, {'iid': 's_10111529', 'name': 'grape tomatoes', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '5 grape tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_1022027', 'name': 'seasoning', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon Italian seasoning'}]}, {'rid': 's_1096186', 'title': 'Quinoa Tabouli Salad', 'inst': 'Prepare quinoa according to the package instructions. Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork. Whisk lemon juice and minced garlic in a small bowl.Gradually stir in olive oil. Add cucumber, tomatoes, herbs, ginger, and scallions to bowl with quinoa; toss to coat.Season to taste with salt and pepper. Drizzle dressing over the salad and fold in to incorporate.Allow to sit and marinate for at least 1 hour before serving.Season salad to taste with salt and pepper.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/JKGT4W6M/a-simple-winter-salad-quinoa-tabouli', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup Quinoa, rinsed well'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'kosher salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon kosher salt plus more'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp fresh lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove minced garlic'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'quality extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup Good Quality Extra Virgin Olive Oil'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Freshly ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11206', 'name': 'hothouse cucumber', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large English hothouse cucumber (diced radish works too)'}, {'iid': 's_10111529', 'name': 'grape tomatoes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pint', 'raw': '1 pint grape tomatoes, halved (or try 2 carrots grated)'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat-leaf parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup chopped flat-leaf parsley'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'scallions', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 scallions, thinly sliced'}]}, {'rid': 's_660290', 'title': 'Slow Cooker Lamb Curry', 'inst': 'Pull out your slow cooker and add everything into the pot with the exception of the yogurt.Now turn on your pot, setting it on low for the next 4-6 hours or high for the next 3-5.When the time is up, open up your slow cooker, grab your yogurt and stir it into the curry. Serve over rice.', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/Z5MXNR2V/slow-cooker-lamb-curry', 'cui': 'indian', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11353', 'name': 'baking potatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 baking Potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_6008', 'name': 'beef broth', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups of beef broth'}, {'iid': 's_1001', 'name': 'butter', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons of Butter'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch of Cilantro, Chopped'}, {'iid': 's_2015', 'name': 'curry', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons of Curry'}, {'iid': 's_98953', 'name': 'fennel powder', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon of fennel powder'}, {'iid': 's_93663', 'name': 'garam masala', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon of Garam Masala'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '3 cloves of Garlic, Minced'}, {'iid': 's_11216', 'name': 'ginger', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon of Ginger'}, {'iid': 's_17059', 'name': 'lamb stew meat', 'qty': 5.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '5 1/2 pounds of Cooked Lamb stew meat'}, {'iid': 's_11260', 'name': 'mushrooms', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '6 ounces of Mushrooms, Chopped'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons of Olive Oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Onion, Diced'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'oregano', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon of Oregano'}, {'iid': 's_1001116', 'name': 'yogurt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup of Plain Yogurt'}, {'iid': 's_2036', 'name': 'rosemary', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon of Rosemary'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon of Salt'}, {'iid': 's_10011693', 'name': 'tomato paste', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'can', 'raw': '1 can of Tomato Paste'}]}, {'rid': 's_1095791', 'title': 'Quinoa Vegetable Salad', 'inst': 'First, chop the iceberg lettuce and place in a large bowl.Wash and dice the tomatoes, cucumber, green peppers, and carrot into pieces.Ad them to the bowl with chopped lettuce.Prepare quinoa according to package instructions. Add the cooked quinoa to the salad bowl.Season with some salt and black pepper.Next, add the olive tapenade, vinegar, and extra virgin olive oil to the bowl and to stir everything very well. Serve.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/GF3WXNG2/quinoa-salad-with-summer-veggies', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 150.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '150 grams uncooked quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_11252', 'name': 'iceberg lettuce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium size', 'raw': '1 medium size iceberg lettuce'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium size', 'raw': '1-2 medium size red tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_11206', 'name': 'cucumber', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium size', 'raw': '1 medium size fresh cucumber'}, {'iid': 's_11333', 'name': 'peppers', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium size', 'raw': '1-2 medium size green peppers'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium size', 'raw': '1 medium size carrot'}, {'iid': 's_98862', 'name': 'olive tapenade', 'qty': 50.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '50 grams olive tapenade'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_2048', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons wine or apple cider vinegar'}]}, {'rid': 's_1096213', 'title': 'Creamy, Healthy Asparagus Soup with Avocado and Fennel', 'inst': "In a large saucepan over medium-low heat, warm oil. Add leek and fennel and a large pinch of salt. Cook, stirring frequently, until fully softened but not browned, 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in bone broth and bring to a simmer. Add asparagus and thyme. Bring to a simmer and cook for 1 minute. Remove a few asparagus tips and use them for garnish. Continue simmering soup until asparagus is soft, 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add lemon juice and avocado.Blend soup using an immersion blender or in batches using a blender until it's smooth. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve. Garnish with reserved asparagus tips, fennel fronds, olive oil and Greek yogurt, if using.", 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/G532D7M3/creamy-healthy-asparagus-soup-with-avocado-and-fennel', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'primal'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil plus more for serving'}, {'iid': 's_11246', 'name': 'leek and pale parts', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large leek white and pale green parts finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11957', 'name': 'fennel bulb', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 fennel bulb thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'kosher salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Kosher salt'}, {'iid': 's_11711111', 'name': 'chicken bone broth', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups Chicken Bone Broth'}, {'iid': 's_11011', 'name': 'asparagus', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 pounds asparagus trimmed and cut into 1-inch pieces'}, {'iid': 's_2049', 'name': 'lemon thyme leaves', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon lemon thyme leaves minced'}, {'iid': 's_9150', 'name': 'lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 lemon juiced'}, {'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 avocado peeled, pitted, and diced'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Freshly ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1256', 'name': 'greek yogurt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '4 tbsp Greek yogurt'}]}, {'rid': 's_1095849', 'title': 'Zucchini Salad Pita Pockets', 'inst': 'Prepare the barley as directed; drain and cool.Shred the zucchini, carrots, onion, drained chickpeas and the parsley, using the shredding blade of the food processor. Place in a bowl and season. Add the barley and toss. Combine the lemon juice and olive oil and add to the salad and toss.Gently mix in the crumbled feta.Fill the pitas and serve.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/76S5YTNK/zucchini-salad-pita-pockets', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20004', 'name': 'barley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of instant barley'}, {'iid': 's_11477', 'name': 'zucchini', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 zucchini'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 carrots'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup Italian parsley'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': '', 'raw': '¼ red onion'}, {'iid': 's_16057', 'name': 'chickpeas', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup chickpeas'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp. salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp. black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_2043', 'name': 'turmeric', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp. turmeric'}, {'iid': 's_2015', 'name': 'curry', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp. curry'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Juice of ½ lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_18042', 'name': 'pita pockets', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 whole wheat pita pockets'}, {'iid': 's_1019', 'name': 'feta', 'qty': 3.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '3.5 oz crumbled feta'}]}, {'rid': 's_642346', 'title': 'Egyptain Cauliflower Side Salad', 'inst': "Separate the cauliflower into medium sized pieces.Steam in a steamer (if you don't have a steamer you can boil the cauliflower whole in water and then cut it into pieces). Place in a bowl. Mix the olive oil, cumin, lemon juice and salt and pepper. Pour over the cauliflower and mix. Garnish with parsley.", 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/C32D4Y44/egyptain-cauliflower-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'cauliflower', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small cauliflower'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon cumin'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Olive oil for drizzling'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt'}]}, {'rid': 's_660368', 'title': 'Smoked Salmon Eggs Benedict With Lemon Dill Hollandaise', 'inst': 'Make Lemon Dill Hollandaise:Fill a medium saucepan about halfway with water, and bring to a gentle simmer over medium heat. Put the egg yolks and water in a heatproof bowl, season with a pinch of dill (if using dried), salt, and pepper. Whisk the ingredients together and then place the bowl on top of the saucepan. Keep stirring the egg mixture for about 5 minutes or until it begins to thicken. Make sure you dont scramble your eggs! Once the eggs are thickened, take the bowl off the water and set aside.Poach the eggs:Fill a medium saucepan with water, add a splash of white vinegar (optional, but this helps hold the whites together which results in nicely shaped eggs) and bring to a gentle simmer. You want tiny bubbles only, not a rolling boil. Gently add eggs to water and poach until deisred doneness.Meanwhile, toast bread. Place toast on plates and top with arugula, spinach and salmon. Place eggs on top of salmon and spoon hollandaise over the top. Garnish with dill, salt and freshly cracked black pepper and serve.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/MZTVJFS5/smoked-salmon-eggs-benedict-with-lemon-dill-hollandaise', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011959', 'name': 'baby arugula', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup baby arugula'}, {'iid': 's_11457', 'name': 'baby spinach', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup baby spinach'}, {'iid': 's_1001', 'name': 'butter', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons butter'}, {'iid': 's_1125', 'name': 'egg yolks', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '3 large egg yolks'}, {'iid': 's_1123', 'name': 'eggs', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 eggs, poached'}, {'iid': 's_2017', 'name': 'dill', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon fresh dill or 1 tsp. dried'}, {'iid': 's_9150', 'name': 'lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_18075', 'name': 'multigrain bread', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'slices', 'raw': '2 slices thick multigrain bread'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_15077', 'name': 'salmon', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '8 ounces smoked salmon'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons water'}, {'iid': 's_6971', 'name': 'worcestershire sauce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce'}]}, {'rid': 's_632718', 'title': 'Armenian Stew', 'inst': 'In a Large Pan, Bring Soaked Apricots and Their Water To a Boil. add Soaked, Drained Garbanzo Beans and 1 C. Water. Bring To a Boil and Cook for 30 Minutes. Add the Lentils, Onions and 4 C. Water To Pot. Bring To a Boil. Lower Heat, Cover and Cook Ubout 2 Hours until Garbanzos Are Tneder. Add 2 t. Malt Syrup. Mix in Well. Serve Over Brown Rice.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/NSYVVMBY/armenian-stew', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9032', 'name': 'apricots soaked in', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup Dried Apricots Soaked in'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup Water for 1 Hour'}, {'iid': 's_16056', 'name': 'garbanzo beans soaked', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup Dried Garbanzo Beans Soaked'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'overnight in water', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Overnight in Water'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '5 cups Water'}, {'iid': 's_10316069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup Lentils'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 Onions Sliced'}, {'iid': 's_19304', 'name': 'malt syrup', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Malt Syrup or Molasses'}]}, {'rid': 's_639957', 'title': 'Colorful Tomato and Spinach Seafood Pasta', 'inst': 'Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Heat oil in large non-stick skillet. Add onion and garlic and cook 3-4 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook another 3-4 minutes until tender.Toss cod with flour and salt and pepper to taste. Add cod to pan and cook another 3 minutes, add another tsp olive oil if necessary. Add chicken broth and wine and cook another 3 minutes, stirring gently to make sauce, but not break up fish. Add spinach and basil and cook another 3-4 minutes until spinach just wilts and sauce has reduced nicely.Top pasta with cod and parmesan cheese.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/CTD7FW43/colorful-tomato-and-spinach-seafood-pasta', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_6194', 'name': 'chicken broth', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup chicken broth'}, {'iid': 's_15015', 'name': 'cod', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '8 ounces cod, cut into bite sized pieces'}, {'iid': 's_20081', 'name': 'flour', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons flour'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons lemon juice, fresh squeezed'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1033', 'name': 'parmesan cheese', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons parmesan cheese , shredded'}, {'iid': 's_10211529', 'name': 'roma tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 large Roma tomatoes, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11677', 'name': 'shallot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large shallot, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups spinach, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_14106', 'name': 'white wine', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup white wine'}, {'iid': 's_20124', 'name': 'pasta', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '4 ounces whole wheat pasta, spaghetti'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'to)', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup to ½ basil (dependent on your taste), roll leaves together and then slice into thin pieces'}]}, {'rid': 's_634792', 'title': 'Beet Salad With Peppers and Lettuce', 'inst': 'Chop the peppers and lettuce into thin slivers.Chop the beets into circular discs, so that they remain the star of the salad and get their moment in the sun. Mix all the salad ingredients. Add the salad dressing just prior to serving. Garnish with sunflower seeds.', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/K53BZ7T2/beet-salad-with-peppers-and-lettuce', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11080', 'name': 'beet', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small beet, peeled and sliced'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon fresh basil, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11252', 'name': 'leave lettuce', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups red leave lettuce'}, {'iid': 's_19911', 'name': 'maple syrup', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon maple syrup'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10011821', 'name': 'orange pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 orange pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red pepper'}, {'iid': 's_12036', 'name': 'sunflower seeds', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': 'Handful of sunflower seeds'}]}, {'rid': 's_637440', 'title': 'Chapchae (Korean Stir-Fried Noodles)', 'inst': 'Cook noodles according to package directions In a large pan or wok over medium heat, heat olive oil and 1 Tbsp sesame oil Add onion slices and garlic and saut for about 1 min Add rest of vegetables and cook for 4-5 min, until the vegetables are half-cooked and still a bit crispy Turn heat to low and add cooked noodles, soy sauce, sugar, and the remaining sesame oil Mix to combine and cook for another 2 min Add salt or more soy sauce if needed (or if you want it a bit sweeter, add a touch more sugar) If using sesame seeds, add them at finish', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/RSDBG48H/chapchae-korean-stir-fried-noodles', 'cui': 'korean', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_99031', 'name': 'sweet potato vermicelli noodles', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '8 ounces sweet potato vermicelli noodles'}, {'iid': 's_11294', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 sweet onion, sliced into thin strips'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11457', 'name': 'baby spinach', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1/2 pound baby spinach, parboiled'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 carrots, julienned'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'scallions', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 scallions, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11260', 'name': 'mushrooms', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '5 mushrooms, sliced (I like to use creminis)'}, {'iid': 's_11477', 'name': 'zucchini', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup zucchini, sliced into half-moons'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_4058', 'name': 'sesame oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons sesame oil'}, {'iid': 's_16124', 'name': 'soy sauce', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons soy sauce'}, {'iid': 's_19335', 'name': 'sugar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon sugar'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt to taste'}]}, {'rid': 's_638741', 'title': 'Chipotle Black Bean Soup with Avocado Cream', 'inst': "Heat the oil in a 4-quart saucepan. Add the carrots and onions and cook until they're tender-crisp, stirring occasionally. Add the peppers and cook and stir for 1 minute.Stir the broth and beans into the saucepan and heat to a boil. Reduce the heat to low. Cook for 25 minutes.Mash the avocado with a fork in a small bowl.  Stir in the sour cream, cilantro and lemon juice.Spoon one-third of the broth mixture into a blender. Cover and blend until the mixture is smooth. Pour the mixture into a large bowl. Repeat twice more with the remaining broth mixture. Return the blended mixture to the saucepan. Cook over medium heat until the mixture is hot and bubbling.  Divide the soup among 8 serving bowls. Top with the avocado mixture.", 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/BLKBQ5DY/chipotle-black-bean-soup-with-avocado-cream', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small ripe avocado, pitted, peeled and cut into cubes (about 1/2 cup)'}, {'iid': 's_16018', 'name': 'black beans', 'qty': 45.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '3 cans (about 15 ounces each) black beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 large carrots, peeled and diced (about 2 cups)'}, {'iid': 's_6194', 'name': 'chicken broth', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups Swanson® Chicken Broth (Regular, Natural Goodness® or Certified Organic)'}, {'iid': 's_99223', 'name': 'chipotle peppers in adobo sauce', 'qty': 7.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '1 can (7 ounces) chipotle peppers in adobo sauce, minced'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro leaves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro leaves'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 large onions, diced (about 2 cups)'}, {'iid': 's_1056', 'name': 'cream', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup sour cream'}]}, {'rid': 's_660926', 'title': 'Spice-Rubbed Lemon Barbecue Salmon', 'inst': 'Place the salmon fillets on a greased, foil-lined baking sheet.Rub the top of the salmon with the barbecue seasoning. Let sit for 10 minutes while you preheat the broiler. Place the baking sheet 4" - 6" from the heating element and broil for 6 - 8 minutes, until cooked through. Remove from the broiler and let sit 5 minutes. Combine the sauce ingredients (barbecue sauce, hoisin sauce, honey and zest of 1/2 lemon) in a small bowl.Spoon the sauce into a small ziplock bag and squeeze down to the corner of the bag. Cut off a very small portion of the corner of the bag and squeeze the sauce generously over the salmon. Serve with a lemon wedge from the other half of the lemon.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/CLKQDV8M/spice-rubbed-lemon-barbecue-salmon', 'cui': 'bbq', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_6150', 'name': 'barbecue sauce', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons barbecue sauce'}, {'iid': 's_1062034', 'name': 'barbecue seasoning', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Barbecue seasoning'}, {'iid': 's_6175', 'name': 'hoisin sauce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon hoisin sauce'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'honey', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons honey'}, {'iid': 's_9150', 'name': 'lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon fillets', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'ounce', 'raw': '2 6-ounce salmon fillets, patted dry'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Kosher salt or sea salt'}]}, {'rid': 's_652607', 'title': 'Mushroom & Cabbage Brown Rice Congee', 'inst': 'In a large pot, combine the rice with four cups of water and a little salt.  Bring the rice and water to a boil. Reduce to low heat, cover and gently simmer for a few hours.  Stir the rice periodically to ensure that it does not stick to the bottom. Add more water if too much evaporates before the rice grains have dissolved enough to provide a good porridge consistency.  Cook the rice three to four hours until you get a thick porridge consistency. As the porridge is finishing, prepare the remaining ingredients.  In a large pan, saut the garlic and ginger for about ten seconds in canola or gape-seed oil over medium heat.  Once the garlic and ginger have released their flavors into the oil, but before they burn, add the chopped mushrooms.  Saut for about 5 minutes until the mushrooms release their water and it has practically evaporated from the pan. Add the tablespoon of soy sauce and cook a few more seconds until absorbed. Place the mushrooms in a covered bowl to keep warm. Without rinsing the pan, add the toasted sesame oil, cabbage and a pinch of salt to the same pan and saut for 1 to 2 minutes.  Allow the cabbage to begin to wilt, but avoid over-cooking it. Serve by dividing the congee into bowls and topping it with the sauted cabbage and mushrooms, chopped green onions and toasted sesame seeds.  Provide soy sauce, rice vinegar and chili oil on the side for dressing the congee. Note: You can quickly make your own chili oil by warming some oil in a pan without allowing it to smoke, and adding fresh or dried crushed chilis to cook for a few minutes without burning.  Once cooked, you can either strain out the chilis, or leave them in.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/54JH8N6L/mushroom-cabbage-brown-rice-congee', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20040', 'name': 'brown rice', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup of brown rice'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'to 6 of water', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups to 6 of water'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large cloves', 'raw': '2 large cloves garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_10211216', 'name': 'ginger', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons fresh ginger, minced'}, {'iid': 's_4517', 'name': 'grapeseed oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon canola or grapeseed oil'}, {'iid': 's_11260', 'name': 'shitake mushrooms', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1/2 pound of shitake mushrooms, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_16124', 'name': 'soy sauce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon soy sauce'}, {'iid': 's_11109', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 cabbage, cut into thin shreds'}, {'iid': 's_4058', 'name': 'sesame oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon toasted sesame oil'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'scallions', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 scallions, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_12023', 'name': 'sesame seeds', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons toasted sesame seeds'}, {'iid': 's_1022053', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt, rice wine vinegar, soy sauce,<'}]}, {'rid': 's_652594', 'title': 'Mung Bean Sprout and Quinoa Salad', 'inst': 'First you sprout!Soak mung beans over night in a jar covered with cheese cloth.  Note: use rubber band to keep cheese cloth in place.Rinse and pour out all of the water from the soaked mung beans.Then place jar diagonally in a bowl, like picture below.Wash mung beans 2 times a day.  You can have them grow 1 to 2 inches in lengthbut, I just kept them short.  I just let it sit for a little bit more than 1.5 days.It is ready to eat after washing.Prepare sprouts Cook quinoa Steam. corn Prepare veggies (mince, slice, and dice) Place quinoa and prepared veggies in a bowl and mix in dressing.  Then, place over a bed of spinach.Top off with corn (optional)Enjoy!', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/WFDCWVHF/mung-bean-sprout-and-quinoa-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2048', 'name': "bragg's all natural apple cider vinegar", 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': "4 tablespoons of Bragg's all natural apple cider vinegar (raw)"}, {'iid': 's_2003', 'name': 'of basil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '2 pinchs of dried basil'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell peppers', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup of bell peppers (diced)'}, {'iid': 's_4047', 'name': 'coconut oil', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '4 tablespoons of cold pressed coconut oil'}, {'iid': 's_20137', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups cooked quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_2012', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '1 pinch of dried cilantro (optional)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove of garlic (minced)'}, {'iid': 's_16080', 'name': 'sprouted mung beans', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups of sprouted mung beans'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup of of red onions (diced)'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'of oregano', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '3 pinchs of dried oregano'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'spinach'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '2 medium tomatoes (diced)'}]}, {'rid': 's_642540', 'title': 'Falafel Burgers', 'inst': 'Combine the chickpeas, onion, garlic, parsley, flour, spices, and salt, and pulse until the mixture is well combined. Form the mixture into 4 large patties. Whisk the tahini paste with the water, lemon juice and zest, salt, and freshly ground black pepper in a mixing bowl. Serve the burgers in pita pockets or on a bun. Top them with tahini sauce, lettuce, and tomato.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/FBWMX8MY/falafel-burgers', 'cui': 'american', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_16058', 'name': 'garbanzo beans', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cans', 'raw': '2 cans garbanzo beans (chickpeas), drained and rinsed'}, {'iid': 's_2009', 'name': 'chili powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon chili powder'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'coriander', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon coriander'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon cumin'}, {'iid': 's_20081', 'name': 'flour', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '4 tablespoons flour'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large handful', 'raw': '1 large handful parsley, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, grated or finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 Zest and juice of lemons'}, {'iid': 's_18413', 'name': 'pita pockets', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 pita pockets'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small red onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_12698', 'name': 'tahini', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup tahini'}, {'iid': 's_2043', 'name': 'turmeric', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 teaspoons turmeric'}, {'iid': 's_4669', 'name': 'vegetable oil', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup vegetable oil'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons water'}]}, {'rid': 's_633097', 'title': 'Autumn In A Bowl Soup', 'inst': 'First peel the squash.  Then cut up squash in cubes. Heat pot up, and add olive oil, then add diced squash.  Saut squash for 5-10 minutes or until softened.  Next add in onion and garlic, saut for another 2-3 minutes, until onion is translucent. Add water, bell pepper, corn, and carrots. Let cook for 40 minutes. Add kale and sage last 15 minutes of cooking. Add salt and pepper to taste.', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/KVZ4WZJQ/autumn-in-a-bowl-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11485', 'name': 'butternut squash', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large butternut squash'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 carrots diced'}, {'iid': 's_11167', 'name': 'ears of corn', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 ears of corn'}, {'iid': 's_99226', 'name': 'sage', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch of fresh sage chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '5 cloves of garlic'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'of kale', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch Large of kale roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 30.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '30 ml/2tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium onion diced'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red bell pepper diced'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '6 cups of water'}]}, {'rid': 's_663177', 'title': 'Thai-Style Mussels', 'inst': 'Scrub the outside of the mussels with a brush. Remove and discard the beards. Heat the oil in a wok or large pan add garlic, lemongrass and chili. Cook until slightly brown and fragrant. Add the mussels to the wok and toss well. Add in chinese rice wine, water, and Thai basil after about 3 minutes. Mix well. Put the lid back on for another 1 minutes or so until all the mussels are open (discard any that stay closed).', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/VMQG43VB/thai-style-mussels', 'cui': 'thai', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_14106', 'name': 'wine', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons dry white wine'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '4 Cloves garlic, pressed or crushed'}, {'iid': 's_11972', 'name': 'stem lemongrass', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 stem lemongrass (white parts only)'}, {'iid': 's_15164', 'name': 'mussels', 'qty': 2.25, 'unit': 'lbs', 'raw': '1 kg ( - 2 1/4 lbs) mussels'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10511819', 'name': 'chilies', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2-3 teaspoons red chilies, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'thai basil leaves', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': 'A handful of Thai basil leaves, roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons Water'}]}, {'rid': 's_642619', 'title': 'Feta Encrusted Salmon', 'inst': 'Pre- Heat oven to 350 FSeason each salmon filet with sea salt and pepper Place on a greased sheet tray Combine olive oil, lemon juice, Panko and chopped dill in a bowl Fold Feta Crumbles into breadcrumb mixture Carefully coat the top of each salmon filet with the breadcrumb mixture Bake in the oven for 8-10 minutes until topping becomes golden brown Serve over couscous with a sprig of dill and fresh lemon', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/PJ28JKQT/fat-free-feta-encrusted-salmon', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2045', 'name': 'dill', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon dill (chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_99254', 'name': 'feta', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '4 oz fat free feta'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice from 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10018079', 'name': 'panko', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup Panko (Japanese bread crumbs)'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon fillets', 'qty': 24.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '4 6 oz. salmon fillets'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Sea Salt'}]}, {'rid': 's_716069', 'title': 'Creamy Vegan Coleslaw Dressed with Avocado', 'inst': 'In a large bowl, toss together the salad ingredients.In a small food processor, pulse together the dressing ingredients until well blended. Toss with the vegetables and serve.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodandspice.com/2015/06/creamy-vegan-coleslaw-dressed-with.html', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 avocado, pitted and peeled'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large carrot, shredded'}, {'iid': 's_2007', 'name': 'celery seed', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon celery seed'}, {'iid': 's_2048', 'name': 'cider vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons cider vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_93831', 'name': 'coconut sugar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons coconut sugar'}, {'iid': 's_1002046', 'name': 'dijon mustard', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons Dijon mustard'}, {'iid': 's_11156', 'name': 'fresh chives', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons fresh chives, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11109', 'name': 'green cabbage', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '3 cups green cabbage, shredded or cut into fine strips'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon ground cumin'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice from 1 lemon (3 tablespoons)'}, {'iid': 's_93690', 'name': 'nutritional yeast', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon nutritional yeast'}, {'iid': 's_10011333', 'name': 'poblano pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 poblano pepper, seeded and cut into fine strips'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea-salt', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'sea salt and fresh cracked black pepper to taste'}]}, {'rid': 's_652078', 'title': 'Miso Soup With Thin Noodles', 'inst': 'After the miso has been prepared, start adding the "stuff" to the soup pot. It can be your preference, but I opted to start with the onions and chives and then added the zucchini, parsnip, carrots, mushrooms and ginger. Cover the pot and let cook on a low flame for 20-30 minutes, tasting as you go. Add the tofu and pasta, allowing the pasta to cook for 8-10 minutes. Taste the soup, adding red pepper and turn off flame when ready. Place spinach on the bottom of your soup bowl. You can also place the spinach directly in the pot, but since it wilts so quickly I usually do it this way. What do you usually add to your Miso Soup? Seriously Soupy Serena', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/BYJ4Q2M5/miso-soup-with-thin-noodles', 'cui': 'asian', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups of water'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': 'bunch of fresh spinach'}, {'iid': 's_10016213', 'name': 'block of tofu', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 of a block of firm tofu'}, {'iid': 's_11260', 'name': 'shitaki mushrooms', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '8 shitaki mushrooms, cut up lengthwise'}, {'iid': 's_11156', 'name': 'chives', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '2 smalls chives, cut into squares'}, {'iid': 's_10511282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 yellow onion, chopped up'}, {'iid': 's_20133', 'name': 'thai kitchen rice noodles', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'package', 'raw': '1/2 package of a of Thai Kitchen Thin Rice Noodles'}, {'iid': 's_11216', 'name': 'ginger', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 ginger'}, {'iid': 's_11298', 'name': 'parsnip', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 parsnip, cut up'}, {'iid': 's_11960', 'name': 'baby carrots', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 baby carrots, cut up'}, {'iid': 's_11477', 'name': 'zucchini', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 zucchini, cut up'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'pepper flakes-taste as you go to adjust flavors', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of red pepper flakes-taste as you go to adjust flavors'}, {'iid': 's_2021', 'name': 'ginger powder-taste as you go to adjust flavors', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of ginger powder-taste as you go to adjust flavors'}]}, {'rid': 's_452116', 'title': 'Rustic Red Wine Spaghetti', 'inst': "In a small skillet, fry the garlic in olive oil until fragrant. Add the mushrooms. When the mushrooms are almost done, add the fresh rosemary, be careful not to let it burn. In a large skillet, fry the chopped savoy cabbage until the desired level of crispiness is achieved. Once the cabbage is nearly done, pour half of the bottle of wine into a pot. Dilute with boiling water until you have enough to cook the pasta in (but try not to dilute it too much). Bring to a boil and salt the water. Add the spaghetti. Drain the pasta, reserving about 1/4 cup of the pasta water. Add the pasta to the skillet with the cabbage. Add the mushrooms and rosemary (you might want to de-glaze the pan they were in with some more wine). Add the reserved wine/water mixture to the pan with the pasta and cabbage. Season with salt and pepper. Add olive oil if it's too dry, and don't forget plenty of Parmesan.", 'serv': 2, 'url': 'http://spoonacular.com/-1393025274242', 'cui': '', 'diets': [], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2063', 'name': 'rosemary', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'fresh rosemary'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic'}, {'iid': 's_11260', 'name': 'mushrooms', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '4 large mushrooms, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 's