 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '3 Tbsp. chopped parsley'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and Pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_9150', 'name': 'lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Olive oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_715392', 'title': 'Easy Slow Cooker Chicken Tortilla Soup', 'inst': 'Add all of your ingredients into the slow cooker and then cook on low for 6 hours. Once finished cooking, scoop into serving bowls and serve with tortilla chips, sour cream, cheese, avocado, or any of your favorite toppings.', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/chicken-tortilla-soup-slow-cooker/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_5062', 'name': 'chicken breast', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 pounds chicken breast'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium onion (finely chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_2009', 'name': 'chili powder', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '2 teaspoon chili powder'}, {'iid': 's_11693', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 28.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '28 ounces crushed tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_6194', 'name': 'chicken broth', 'qty': 24.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '24 ounces chicken broth'}, {'iid': 's_11172', 'name': 'kernel corn', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '15 ounces kernel corn (drained)'}, {'iid': 's_31015', 'name': 'chilis', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '4 ounces green chilis (diced)'}, {'iid': 's_16015', 'name': 'black beans', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '15 ounces black beans (drained)'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup cilantro (freshly chopped)'}]}, {'rid': 's_640338', 'title': 'Cracked Wheat Salad with Dates & Tahini Yogurt', 'inst': 'For Tahini Yogurt: dry roast ground cumin and coriander in a pan for a few minutes until they start getting fragrant. In a mixing bowl, add yogurt and tahini and mix well. Now add cumin, coriander, juice and zest of 1 lemon, olive oil, and salt to taste and mix well to form a thick paste-like mixture. Set aside.For Assembling the Salad: In a big salad bowl mix everything and season with little salt (just be careful as the yogurt topping also has salt in it). Serve in individual salad bowls,  putting a dollop of the tahini yogurt and sprinkling some toasted sesame seeds. Tastes best at room temperature.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/6PVSJLCP/cracked-wheat-salad-with-dates-tahini-yogrt', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10116070', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup red lentils, cooked'}, {'iid': 's_93684', 'name': 'cracked wheat', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup cracked wheat, cooked'}, {'iid': 's_9087', 'name': 'dates', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup dates, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup fresh parsley, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1256', 'name': 'greek yogurt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup greek yogurt'}, {'iid': 's_1002013', 'name': 'ground coriander', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp ground coriander'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp ground cumin'}, {'iid': 's_9150', 'name': 'lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small red onion, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_12023', 'name': 'sesame seeds', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'sesame seeds'}, {'iid': 's_1002028', 'name': 'paprika', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp sweet paprika'}, {'iid': 's_12698', 'name': 'tahini', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup tahini'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'zucchini', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium zucchini, diced and grilled in some olive oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_655806', 'title': 'Pesto & Yogurt Pasta', 'inst': 'In a food processor, blend parsley, garlic, nuts and oil until smooth. Mix in yogurt and cheese.  Season with salt and pepper.Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling water, stirring occasionally until al dente.Toss pasta and pesto sauce together in a large bowl.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/Z4QRF6N7/pesto-yogurt-pasta', 'cui': '', 'diets': [], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11420420', 'name': 'farfalle', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '½ lb. Farfalle (use your favorite pasta or spaghetti)'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat leaf parsley', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1½ cups flat leaf Parsley'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '3 cloves garlic'}, {'iid': 's_1117', 'name': 'yogurt', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup low-fat plain yogurt (can be substituted with Greek yogurt)'}, {'iid': 's_12135', 'name': 'nuts', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup mixed nuts'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Olive Oil'}, {'iid': 's_1032', 'name': 'parmesan cheese', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt & pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt & Pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_653549', 'title': 'Okra Tomato Salad', 'inst': 'Remove ends of okra pods, discard. Slice okra. Place okra in a basket and steam for five to seven minutes. Roughly chop a tomato. When okra is cooked, place in a bowl and toss with tomato. Season with salt and pepper. In a small bowl whisk basil into balsamic vinegar. Drizzle over okra and tomato.', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/XNX4G5JC/the-essence-of-okra', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11278', 'name': 'two-inch long okra pods', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '10-15 two-inch long okra pods'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large tomato, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'serving', 'raw': 'Salt and Pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'leaves', 'raw': '3 leaves of basil, finely diced'}, {'iid': 's_2069', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar'}]}, {'rid': 's_660490', 'title': 'Sockeye Salmon on Kiwi & Lemon Puree', 'inst': 'Season salmon fillets with seasoning of choice and let sit at room temperature for 10 minutes. Heat non-stick frying pan to medium-high with 2 tbsp olive oil. Place salmon fillets (skin down) on frying pan for about 7, 8 minutes. Reduce heat to medium and flip salmon over, cook about 6, 7 minutes. Cook until browned or original pink coloration has disappeared. Generally we cook longer skin side down to prevent the fish from flaking or falling apart. Meanwhile, prepare kiwi puree by adding kiwi pieces, lemonade, and lime juice into a food processor. Pulse until finely pureed thoroughly into a runny consistency. Add kiwi puree to serving dish and top with salmon fillet. Garnish with thin lemon strips/zest or curled scallion strips.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/2H25GCSX/sockeye-salmon-on-kiwi-lemon-puree', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'sockeye salmon fillets', 'qty': 32.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '•4 (about 8 oz. each) sockeye salmon fillets'}, {'iid': 's_9148', 'name': 'kiwis', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '•2 kiwis, peeled'}, {'iid': 's_99184', 'name': 'lemonade', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '•1/2 cup lemonade'}, {'iid': 's_1092034', 'name': 'lemon and pepper seasoning', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '•1 tsp lemon and pepper seasoning (or fish seasoning)'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '•2 tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1029150', 'name': 'lemon wedges', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '•4 lemon wedges'}, {'iid': 's_9156', 'name': 'lemon zest', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': '•lemon zest (garnish; optional)'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'scallion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '•1 scallion, thin strips curled (garnish; optional)'}]}, {'rid': 's_637919', 'title': 'Chicken and Roasted Broccoli Salad With Goat Cheese', 'inst': 'Heat oven to 500 degrees and place a sturdy baking sheet on the lowest rack. Heat 2 T olive oil, sliced garlic, and pepper flakes in a small skillet over med-low heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until the garlic is soft and begins to turn golden brown, about 5-7 minutes. Add chicken to the skillet and cook until heated through, about 3-5 minutes. Remove chicken-garlic mixture from heat; stir in oregano and lemon juice.Toss roasted vegetables with the chicken-garlic mixture and an additional 2 T of olive oil in a large salad bowl. Gently fold in the goat cheese crumbles and serve immediately with lemon wedges.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/LL6GDZBZ/chicken-and-roasted-broccoli-salad-with-goat-cheese', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'head of broccoli', 'qty': 1.75, 'unit': 'lbs', 'raw': '1 inch large head of broccoli (about 1 ¾ lbs), cut into 1- 2 florets'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 garlic cloves, sliced thinly'}, {'iid': 's_1159', 'name': 'goat cheese', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '4 ounces of goat cheese, crumbled'}, {'iid': 's_1029150', 'name': 'juice from a lemon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 juice from a lemon (about 2 T), plus additional lemon wedges for garnish'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'oregano', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'of dried oregano'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '1 pinch pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 red bell pepper, cut into thin strips'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'a couple of pepper flakes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '1 pinch a couple of crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '1 pinch salt'}, {'iid': 's_1005114', 'name': 'chicken', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups cooked, shredded chicken'}, {'iid': 's_19335', 'name': 'sugar', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon sugar'}]}, {'rid': 's_655219', 'title': 'Peanut Butter And Chocolate Oatmeal', 'inst': 'Microwave all ingredients in a small bowl or mug for 1 minute, stir and enjoy! Serve with crushed peanuts or almonds for some extra crunch!', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/JCCVHSNP/peanut-butter-and-chocolate-oatmeal', 'cui': 'southern', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_8402', 'name': 'cooking oats', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup quick cooking oats'}, {'iid': 's_19165', 'name': 'cocoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon unsweetened cocoa'}, {'iid': 's_19912', 'name': 'agave', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon agave'}, {'iid': 's_16097', 'name': 'crunchy peanut butter', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon organic crunchy peanut butter'}, {'iid': 's_1085', 'name': 'non-fat milk', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup non-fat milk'}]}, {'rid': 's_657679', 'title': 'Quinoa Salad With Avocado, Asparagus and Sun Dried Tomatoes', 'inst': 'Rinse quinoa under cold running water for a minute or two to get rid of the bitter aftertaste. Transfer to a pot or rice cooker, add 2 cups of water, salt, cover and bring to a boil. Lower down the heat and cook 15 min or until water is absorbed.In another pot bring water to a boil, add asparagus and simmer 5-8 min or until soft.When ready cool down the quinoa and asparagus. Meanwhile chop all the veggie ingredients.Prepare the dressing by simply mixing all of its ingredients (lemon juice, 2 tbs olive oil, 1 garlic clove, 1 tsp italian seasoning, 1/2 tsp honey, pinch of salt) in a bowl.In a bowl combine quinoa, avocado, asparagus, sun dried tomatoes and shallots. Pour the dressing and mix until all is combined.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/NRZZ4FGK/quinoa-salad-with-avocado-asparagus-and-sun-dried-tomatoes', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11011', 'name': 'asparagus', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup asparagus cut into few inch pieces'}, {'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 avocado'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic clove', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 garlic clove minced'}, {'iid': 's_19912', 'name': 'honey', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon honey or agave'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 Juice of lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_1042027', 'name': 'herb seasoning', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon Italian herb seasoning'}, {'iid': 's_11677', 'name': 'shallots', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 shallots'}, {'iid': 's_11955', 'name': 'sun tomatoes', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup sun dried tomatoes'}]}, {'rid': 's_662654', 'title': 'Sweet-N-Smoky Salmon With Ginger Mahogany Rice', 'inst': 'Place the salmon in bowl, or large zip bag with soy sauce, liquid smoke and brown sugar. Let it marinate for at least 1 hourbut you could marinate over night! When ready to use, preheat the grill or an iron skillet to high heat.In a medium sauce pan, over high heat, toast the rice in 1 Tb. of oil for 2 minutes. Then add the chicken stock and a large pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Lower the heat to a simmer and cover. Simmer the rice for about 40 minutesor as directed on the package.Meanwhile, peel the ginger and cut into thin strips. (julienne) Heat a small skillet over medium-high. Add 1 Tb. of oil to the skillet. When the oil is hot, drop the ginger in and pan-fry for 1-2 minutes, moving with a spatula, until they are light brown. Remove from the pan and drain on a paper towel. Sprinkle with salt.While the rice is cooking, CAREFULLY brush the grill with vegetable oil. (You could also use grill spray.) Pepper the salmon and place it on the grill, top-side-down. Cook 3 minutes.Flip, then carefully sprinkle the tops with a little extra brown sugar and grill for another 3-5 minutesuntil just cooked through.Cover with foil and let them rest for 5-10 minutes before serving.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/2HG3YCHN/sweet-n-smoky-salmon-with-ginger-mahogany-rice', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'fodmap friendly', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_19334', 'name': 'brown sugar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup Brown sugar, firmly packed'}, {'iid': 's_6172', 'name': 'chicken stock', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups chicken stock'}, {'iid': 's_11216', 'name': 'ginger', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'inches', 'raw': '3 inches piece of ginger'}, {'iid': 's_93627', 'name': 'liquid smoke', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 teaspoons liquid smoke'}, {'iid': 's_4042', 'name': 'peanut oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tb', 'raw': '2 Tb. peanut oil, separated'}, {'iid': 's_20444', 'name': 'mahogany rice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup mahogany rice'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'fillet', 'raw': '4 Salmon fillets'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and Pepper'}, {'iid': 's_16124', 'name': 'soy sauce', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Soy sauce'}]}, {'rid': 's_664754', 'title': 'Veggie-Quinoa Stuffed Chilis', 'inst': 'HEAT THE OVEN TO 450* PLACE THE QUINOA, OJ AND STOCK INTO A SAUCEPAN. COOK UNTIL ALL THE LIQUID IS ABSORBED. ADD THE SALT TO TASTE. IN A SMALL SKILLET, SAUTE THE MUSHROOMS UNTIL LIGHTLY BROWNED. REMOVE FROM HEAT AND ADD THE SPINACH. STIR TO COMBINE AND SET ASIDE. PLACE THE 1/2 SQUASH IN A GLASS PIE PAN WITH ABOUT A 1/4 INCH OF WATER. COVER WITH PLASTIC WRAP AND MICROWAVE FOR 8-10 MINUTES UNTIL JUST SOFT BUT NOT MUSHY. DICED THE SQUASH INTO 1/4  CUBES AND SET ASIDE TO COOL SLIGHTLY. ADD THE CURRANTS, CUMIN AND CORIANDER TO THE QUINOA, STIR TO COMBINE. ADD THE MUSHROOMS & SPINACH, FETA  AND THE SQUASH. TOSS LIGHTLY. FILL THE PEELED & SEEDED POBLANOS WITH THE QUINOA MIXTURE AND PLACE ON A COOKIE SHEET. BAKE FOR 10-15 MINUTES UNTIL THE MIXTURE IS HOT AND THE CHEESE IS SOFT. SERVE ON A POOL OF THE TOMATO SAUCE OR PAINT WITH THE MANGO VINAIGRETTE.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/L2QPZ4YM/veggie-quinoa-stuffed-chilis', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011333', 'name': 'poblano peppers- roasted', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '8 POBLANO PEPPERS- ROASTED, PEELED& SEEDED'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup QUINOA'}, {'iid': 's_9206', 'name': 'orange juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup ORANGE JUICE'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable stock', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup CHICKEN OR VEGETABLE STOCK'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon SALT'}, {'iid': 's_11260', 'name': 'shitake mushrooms', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 SHITAKE MUSHROOMS- FINELY DICED'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon OLIVE OIL'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup SPINACH THINLY SLICED'}, {'iid': 's_11485', 'name': 'butternut squash', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 BUTTERNUT SQUASH'}, {'iid': 's_9085', 'name': 'currants', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup DRIED CURRANTS'}, {'iid': 's_12142', 'name': 'pecans', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup TOASTED PECANS'}, {'iid': 's_1002013', 'name': 'ground coriander', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon GROUND CORIANDER'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon GROUND CUMIN'}, {'iid': 's_1019', 'name': 'oz feta into dice', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 OZ FETA DICED INTO SMALL DICE'}, {'iid': 's_11549', 'name': 'sauce: we used roas ed tomato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': 'SAUCE: WE USED ROASTED TOMATO, BUT A MANGO SALSA WOULD BE LOVELY!'}]}, {'rid': 's_633624', 'title': 'Baked Fried Chicken With Cauliflower Mash', 'inst': "For marinade:Fillet chicken breast in half to make thinner pieces, and cut in half again to make smaller pieces. Whisk all marinade ingredients (except for the chicken) in large bowl. Add chicken and coat in marinade.Chill overnight for more intense flavor. But if you are short on time (which I usually am) it is ok to use right away as well.For breading:Preheat to 450F Mix breading ingredients large bowl. Place wire rack on baking sheets. Remove chicken breast from bowl and place in coating mixture. Transfer to rack. Repeat with remaining chicken breasts.- Place chicken breasts on rack and spray with olive oil . Cut up cauliflower in small pieces. Place in large saut pan with about 1 cup of water (enough to cover the bottom of pan, plus a little extra to make sure it doesn't all evaporate)Cook until tender. Combine cauliflower with buttermilk, sour cream, ricotta and salt and pepper.In batches, place in blender and puree until smooth. (if it is having a hard time blending, add either some chicken or vegetable stock, or even more buttermilk)", 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/GPDLDNDC/baked-fried-chicken-with-cauliflower-mash', 'cui': 'southern', 'diets': [], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1230', 'name': 'buttermilk', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup buttermilk'}, {'iid': 's_1230', 'name': 'buttermilk', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups buttermilk'}, {'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'cauliflower', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'heads', 'raw': '2 heads of cauliflower'}, {'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'cauliflower mash', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Cauliflower Mash'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'cayenne pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper'}, {'iid': 's_5006', 'name': 'chicken', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Chicken (Baked chicken recipe adapted from Epicurious.com)'}, {'iid': 's_1032046', 'name': 'dijon mustard', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons Dijon mustard'}, {'iid': 's_1002024', 'name': 'mustard', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 teaspoons dry mustard'}, {'iid': 's_20081', 'name': 'flour', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '6 tablespoons flour'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 garlic cloves, pressed'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_9156', 'name': 'lemon peel', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons lemon peel'}, {'iid': 's_1179', 'name': 'cream', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup low fat sour cream'}, {'iid': 's_10018079', 'name': 'panko', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups whole wheat panko'}, {'iid': 's_2028', 'name': 'paprika', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon Paprika'}, {'iid': 's_1032', 'name': 'parmesan cheese', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'iid': 's_1036', 'name': 'ricotta', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup low fat ricotta'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1055062', 'name': 'chicken breast', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 pounds boneless, skinless chicken breast'}, {'iid': 's_2049', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon minced thyme'}]}, {'rid': 's_659060', 'title': 'Salmon Confit with Lemongrass Sauce', 'inst': 'Begin by preheating the oven to 120C. An efficient oven is important for this dish. If the oven is too cold, the fish will not get cooked. If the oven tends to get too hot, the fish will be roasted and overcooked. If you are uncertain, then think about whether your cookies/cakes are usually overdone or underdone when you follow a recipe exactly. If they are always overdone, then you can turn down the temperature to 110C.Get the freshest salmon fillets you can get your hands on. The thick ones are the nicest for this dish. Add 2 tablespoons of extra virgin olive oil to the salmon fillets and rub it all over the fish.Season generously with salt and pepper. About 1/2 teaspoon each of salt and pepper. I usually use Masterfoods Garlic Pepper for each time that I need salt and pepper. Rub the seasonings all over the fish.Slice two lemons into thick slices, discarding the ends. Lay the slices of lemons on a baking tray lined with baking paper. Place the salmon fillets on top of the lemon slices. If you have left the skin on for the fillets, then make sure its skin side down. Place the salmon fillets in the oven and cook for 25 mins. If the salmon fillets are very thick, cook a little longer for another 3 to 5 mins.While the fish is cooking, prepare the vegetable medley and sauce.Peel a large carrot and diagonally slice into thin slices.Wash and pluck the leaves of a bunch of spinach. I used about 150g of baby spinach. Heat a deep saucepan and add 1 tablespoon of cooking oil. Keep the heat at medium heat.When the oil is hot, add 1 tablespoon of butter.When the butter has melted, add the carrots and stir fry for a minute to cook and soften the carrots. I like them slightly crunchy so I dont cook them for too long here. Keep the heat at medium. Remove the cooked carrot slices and set aside in a warm place.In the same pan, add 1 tablespoon of minced garlic. Stir fry for 20 seconds. Add the spinach leaves. Stir fry at medium heat. Add salt and pepper to taste. About 1/2 teaspoon each of salt and pepper. I used Masterfoods Garlic Pepper seasonings instead again.Stir fry the spinach till its soft and wilted. Careful not to overcook as they would lose their natural pretty green colour.Dish up the cooked spinach and set aside in a warm place.Now make the sauce.Peel off the hard outer layer of 2 stalks of lemon grass. Slice into 2 inch long pieces and using the back of your knife, bash the lemongrass and bruise the slightly for the fragrance and flavours to emit. Add 1 tablespoon of butter to a small saucepan.When the butter has melted and is bubbling slightly, add the lemongrass. Cook at medium heat for 30 seconds. Add 150ml of fresh liquid cream. Let the mixture come to a gentle rolling boil. Add 1 teaspoon of liquid chicken stock concentrate. Or you can use 1/2 cube of chicken stock bouillon. Stir it in well, and do a taste check. If its not salty enough, add more chicken stock. Whisk the sauce as it boils and thickens.After a couple of minutes, the sauce would have thickened. Remove the lemongrass. Add 1 tablespoon of lemon juice. I usually use a strainer and squeeze a lemon directly over the sauce. Do a taste check. Add more lemon juice if necessary. Whisk well to combine.The salmon should be done by now. Remove them from the oven.Plate your dish but placing some spinach and carrots at the bottom of a plate or shallow dish.Gently place the salmon fillet on top. Drizzle a generous amount of sauce around the fish. Garnish with chives.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/DKLPSG8W/salmon-confit-with-lemon-grass-sauce', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'pescatarian', 'ketogenic'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1001', 'name': 'butter', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon butter'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large carrot'}, {'iid': 's_6080', 'name': 'liquid chicken stock', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon liquid chicken stock (or 1/2 cube of chicken stock cubes)'}, {'iid': 's_11156', 'name': 'chives to garnish', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Chives to garnish'}, {'iid': 's_4582', 'name': 'cooking oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon cooking oil'}, {'iid': 's_1053', 'name': 'cream', 'qty': 150.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '150ml fresh cream'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon minced garlic'}, {'iid': 's_11972', 'name': 'lemon grass', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'stalks', 'raw': '2 stalks of lemon grass (ends only, outer leaves removed)'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_9150', 'name': 'lemons', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 large lemons'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon fillets', 'qty': 400.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '400g – 450g salmon fillets (preferably skinless)'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11457', 'name': 'spinach leaves', 'qty': 150.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '150g – 200g spinach leaves (I used baby spinach leaves)'}]}, {'rid': 's_648627', 'title': 'Juicy & Tender ~ Pork Loin Roast', 'inst': 'Place the garlic, parsley, tomatoes, olive oil and black pepper in the food processor and give a few good chops. Place the pork in a baking pan and top with the chopped veggies. Add the chicken broth to the pan with the bay leaves and roast in the oven. You may add more broth to the pan as the broth dries. Bake about 20 minutes per pound ~ about 1 hour.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/VRMLC8F3/juicy-tender-pork-loin-roast', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'whole 30'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 bay leaves'}, {'iid': 's_6194', 'name': 'chicken broth', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup of chicken broth'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1/2 bunch of fresh parsley'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '4 cloves of fresh garlic'}, {'iid': 's_10111529', 'name': 'grape tomatoes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of grape tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup of olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'dashes', 'raw': 'Dashes of black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10225', 'name': 'pork loin roast', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '3 pounds Pork Loin Roast'}]}, {'rid': 's_648985', 'title': 'Knock Your Socks Off Stuffed Potatoes With Broccoli and Mushrooms', 'inst': 'Prick potatoes with a fork and microwave on high for 10 minutes until tender. Allow to cool enough to handle then, cut in halve and scoop out the middle into a medium bowl.While potatoes are cooking, heat oil over medium heat and saute onion, broccoli, mushrooms, garlic and thyme for 10 minutes until tender.Mash potato pulp with yogurt and parsley with salt and pepper to your taste.Stuff potato halves with potato pulp. Top with broccoli mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan.Broil until cheese bubbles.Top with sour cream.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/RZCY5NHT/knock-your-socks-off-stuffed-potatoes-with-broccoli-and-mushrooms', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011090', 'name': 'broccoli florets', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups broccoli florets, rough chopped'}, {'iid': 's_6194', 'name': 'chicken broth', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup chicken broth'}, {'iid': 's_11266', 'name': 'crimini mushrooms', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups Crimini mushrooms, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_1118', 'name': 'yogurt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup fat free plain yogurt'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/3 cup chopped onion'}, {'iid': 's_1033', 'name': 'parmesan cheese', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '4 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, shredded'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons parsley, minced'}, {'iid': 's_1179', 'name': 'cream', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '4 tablespoons light sour cream'}, {'iid': 's_2049', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon thyme'}, {'iid': 's_10211362', 'name': 'yukon gold potatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '4 large Yukon gold potatoes'}]}, {'rid': 's_1095745', 'title': 'Mushroom Hummus Crostini', 'inst': 'To make the hummus, place all ingredients in a food processor and blend until smooth. Adjust the amount of water and harissa pasta depending on how thick and spicy you want your hummus. It should still be spreadable. Set the hummus aside.Slice the mushrooms and fry in a shallow pan until they are golden and crispy. Once they are ready, push them to one side of the pan and add the spinach to wilt.To assemble the crostini, spread some hummus on a slice of the bread (you can toast it if you like), then top with some spinach and mushrooms. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/DMRJSD86/mushroom-crostini-with-harissa-hummus', 'cui': 'mediterranean', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10018029', 'name': 'crusty bread', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'loaf', 'raw': '1 loaf crusty bread'}, {'iid': 's_11260', 'name': 'mushrooms', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound mushrooms'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'handfuls', 'raw': '2-3 handfuls Fresh Spinach'}, {'iid': 's_16058', 'name': 'chickpeas', 'qty': 14.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 14oz can chickpeas'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp Lemon Juice'}, {'iid': 's_12698', 'name': 'tahini', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp Tahini'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2-3 tbsp Water'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4 tsp Ground Cumin'}, {'iid': 's_1006972', 'name': 'harissa', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2-3 tbsp Harissa'}]}, {'rid': 's_662231', 'title': 'Summer Kale, Orange & Pomegranate Salad with Moscato Dressing', 'inst': 'Assemble the Salad: Over medium heat, toast sunflower seeds in a small skillet until lightly golden; Cool.In a large bowl, combine kale, parsley, butter lettuce,  cabbage, orange segments, onion, bell pepper & sunflower seeds.Season with Kosher salt & fresh cracked black pepper to taste.In a small bowl, whisk together all the dressing ingredients & lightly spoon dressing over kale mixture to lightly coat.Plating: On a chilled serving plate, place a 3 x 4 metal plating/forming ring;  Spoon kale salad mixture into the ring & lightly pressing down to compact salad; Place 2 orange segments on top.Carefully remove plating ring. Sprinkle fresh pomegranate seeds around the plate with a quarter size drop of pomegranate molasses. Serve immediately or refrigerate for up to 2 days.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/GBVC4L73/summer-kale-orange-pomegranate-salad-with-moscato-dressing', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11250', 'name': 'butter lettuce', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'head', 'raw': '1/2 head of butter lettuce, cored & chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1032046', 'name': 'dijon mustard', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon Dijon Mustard'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'dinosaur kale', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1/2 bunch dinosaur kale, thick stems removed & leaves thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_14140', 'name': 'presto moscato dolce', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '6 tablespoons Presto Moscato Dolce'}, {'iid': 's_9206', 'name': 'orange juice', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons freshly squeezed orange juice'}, {'iid': 's_9200', 'name': 'to 2 oranges', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 to 2 oranges, peeled & segmented'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'curley parsley', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup curley parsley, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_99279', 'name': 'garnish: pomegranate molasses', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Garnish: Pomegranate molasses, Fresh pomegranate seeds'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 red bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_11112', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup shredded red cabbage'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1/2 small red onion, thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_12036', 'name': 'sunflower seeds', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup sunflower seeds, lightly toasted'}]}, {'rid': 's_652775', 'title': 'Mussels With Tomatoes and Fennel', 'inst': 'Pick over the mussels, removing any beards. Slice the onion. Remove the root end and stalks from the fennel and save any feathery bits for garnish. Thinly slice the bulb. Cut a cross in the bottom of each tomato and pour boiling water over them. Let stand for a minute then slip off the skins and remove the cores. Heat the olive oil and saut the onion, fennel and garlic over a gentle heat until tender. Turn the heat up to medium and add the fennel seeds and chilli flakes. Cook for a minute then add the wine and stir for a further minute. Add quartered tomatoes and the sugar, stir then cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Check the seasoning and add salt and freshly ground pepper as necessary. Add a handful of chopped basil. Tip in the mussels, cover and steam for five minutes. The mussels are ready when the shells open. Discard any that remain closed. Give the mussels a stir, sprinkle over the parsley (and chopped fennel fronds if using) and serve immediately in deep bowls with crusty bread.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/YTM7WGK5/mussels-with-tomatoes-and-fennel', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large onion'}, {'iid': 's_11957', 'name': 'fennel', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium head', 'raw': '1 medium head of fennel'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, smashed and roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '8 tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_2018', 'name': 'fennel seeds', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon fennel seeds'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'chilli flakes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon chilli flakes'}, {'iid': 's_14106', 'name': 'white wine', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup white wine'}, {'iid': 's_19335', 'name': 'sugar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon sugar'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil - greek basil if you have it', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': 'handful chopped basil - Greek basil if you have it'}, {'iid': 's_15164', 'name': 'mussels', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'kg', 'raw': '1 kg mussels'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat leaf parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small bunch', 'raw': '1 small bunch flat leaf parsley'}]}, {'rid': 's_1095806', 'title': 'Spanish style salmon fillets', 'inst': 'Cut onions into wedges and slice bell peppers into strips. Put the croutons, olives, onions, and peppers on a baking sheet. Add the smoked paprika, salt, pepper and 3 tablespoons of the olive oil and toss until everything is evenly coated. Bake in the oven at 400F for about 15 minutes.Rub the salmon fillets with the remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil and season with the remaining salt and pepper. Arrange the fillets among the vegetables and croutons on the baking sheet. Bake for 10-15 minutes or until the salmon is cooked.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/JS5W8D53/spanish-style-salmon-fillets', 'cui': 'spanish', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'whole 30', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_18242', 'name': 'croutons', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups croutons'}, {'iid': 's_1029195', 'name': 'olives', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¾ cup pitted green olives'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 red onions, cut into wedges'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell peppers', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 red bell peppers, seeded and cut into thick strips'}, {'iid': 's_1012028', 'name': 'paprika', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp smoked paprika'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'coarse sea salt', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 ½ tsp coarse sea salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 ½ tsp ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '5 Tbs olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon fillets', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound salmon fillets'}]}, {'rid': 's_658357', 'title': 'Rigatoni With Sweet Sausages In Creamy Tomato Sauce', 'inst': 'Bring a large pot of salted water to boil. Chop the onions, garlic, and set aside. Chop the leek (cut in 1/2 lengthwise first & make sure to rinse very well!!) and set aside (separate from the onions & garlic). Chop the sage & set aside separately as well. To easily remove the casings, lightly slice each sausage lengthwise. Peel off with your fingers. In a large pan over medium/high heat, cook the sausages until they are a nice golden brown. While cooking, break apart the mixture until it looks like ground meat. Take the meat out of the pan and save it in a bowl. Add 2 tbsp olive oil and add the sage to the pan. Cook for a minute, add the leeks & cayenne pepper. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes and put the meat back in the pan. When the leek is cooked, turn off the heat and keep in the mixture in the pan. In a medium size pot over medium/ high heat, add 1 tbsp olive oil, thyme, garlic & onions. Cook for 3-4 minutes, until onions are translucent. Add crushed tomatoes, lower the heat and simmer for about 20 minutes (with a lose lid, otherwise the sauce will splatter all over your kitchen walls!) Add sugar and about 1 tsp kosher salt (1/2 tsp for regular salt), stir and cook for another 2 minutes. Puree the tomatoes until smooth. Add milk and butter, and stir. Keep the heat on very low or turn off until you are ready to serve. When rigatoni is cooked, add to the hot pan with the sausage mixture. Stir well, add a little olive oil if it looks dry. Plate and add tomato sauce to the pasta. Serve this way or with parmesan.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/B88DK7YQ/rigatoni-with-sweet-sausages-in-creamy-tomato-sauce', 'cui': '', 'diets': [], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1017063', 'name': 'sausages', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 sweet sausages'}, {'iid': 's_11246', 'name': 'leek', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 leek, well rinsed and sliced on the bias'}, {'iid': 's_99226', 'name': 'sage', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon fresh sage, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 garlic cloves, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1/2 medium onion, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11693', 'name': 'canned tomatoes', 'qty': 28.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 can (28 oz) crushed tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_11220420', 'name': 'rigatoni', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound rigatoni'}, {'iid': 's_1174', 'name': 'milk', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup 2% milk'}, {'iid': 's_2042', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon dried thyme'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'cayenne pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1001', 'name': 'butter', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon butter'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_19335', 'name': 'sugar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons sugar'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt& pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt& pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_644108', 'title': 'Fusilli With Zucchini Flowers, Ricotta and Saffron', 'inst': 'Fusilli with zucchini flowers, ricotta and saffron What do I need for 2 people Wash and finely chop the onion  dry them gently in a pan with a drizzle of extra virgin olive oil, a pinch of salt and the sliced almonds.Discard the stem and pistil of the flowers of pumpkin, cut into strips and add them to the mixture, stir briefly and turn off.Drop the Fusilloro in plenty of boiling salted water and cook for 9 minutes (al dente).In a bowl mix the ricotta with saffron, add a spoonful of pasta cooking water to obtain a smooth cream, add salt and pepper. Drain the pasta into the pan with the fried zucchini flowers, add saffron cream and mix gently. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/FPKPM74C/fusilli-with-zucchini-flowers-ricotta-and-saffron', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10112061', 'name': 'almonds', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'sliced almonds'}, {'iid': 's_4582', 'name': 'oil evo', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Oil Evo'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red onion'}, {'iid': 's_1036', 'name': 'ricotta cheese', 'qty': 100.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '100 grams of ricotta cheese'}, {'iid': 's_2037', 'name': 'saffron', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'packet', 'raw': '1 packet of saffron'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt'}, {'iid': 's_11477', 'name': 'zucchini flowers', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '12 zucchini flowers'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'fusilloro verrigni o fusilloni', 'qty': 160.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '160 grams Fusilloro Verrigni o fusilloni'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'fusilloro verrigni o fusilloni', 'qty': 160.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '160 grams Fusilloro Verrigni o fusilloni'}]}, {'rid': 's_636212', 'title': 'Broccoli Rabe with Tomatoes, Anchovies & Spaghetti', 'inst': 'Cut the stems of the broccoli off, about 1 inch. Place the broccoli in a saucepot of boiling water for about 3-4 minutes. Drain and set aside. Heat a large frying pan with a few drizzles of olive oil and place the garlic, red pepper flakes and tomatoes in the pan to saut until the tomatoes are soft and the garlic fragrant. Add the broccoli rabe and continue to saut for a few more minutes. Add the anchovies and toss. Continue to saut on low while preparing the spaghetti.When preparing the spaghetti, add a  cup of the water from the spaghetti to the broccoli rabe. Drain the spaghetti. In a serving plate drizzle olive oil and grate Romano cheese at the bottom of the plate. Add the spaghetti, top with the broccoli rabe. Drizzle a little olive oil over the top, squeeze the juice of 1 lemon over the top and finish with freshly grated Romano cheese.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/NN7GPTYR/broccoli-rabe-with-tomatoes-anchovies-spaghetti', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11096', 'name': 'broccoli rabe', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch of broccoli rabe'}, {'iid': 's_15002', 'name': 'anchovies', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '2 oz. can of anchovies in oil'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '6 cloves of garlic – chopped'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Juice of lemon'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'pepper flakes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'dashes', 'raw': 'Dashes of red pepper flakes'}, {'iid': 's_1038', 'name': 'romano cheese', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Grated Romano Cheese'}, {'iid': 's_11420420', 'name': 'spaghetti', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'box', 'raw': '1 box of your favorite spaghetti'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 tomatoes – chopped'}]}, {'rid': 's_635055', 'title': 'Black Bean and Cheese Stuffed Bell Peppers', 'inst': 'Pre heat oven to 350 degrees F Cut tops off of each red pepper and clean out insides. Mix brown rice, corn, onions, black beans, salsa, cumin, salt, pepper, and 1/2 cup of the shredded cheddar. Mix well.Fill each bell pepper Using the last 1 cup of shredded cheddar sprinkling over tops of each bell pepper.In your baking pan pour about 1/4 inch of water or less Place bell peppers in and bake for 30 minutes', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TGTLYH2Q/black-bean-and-cheese-stuffed-bell-peppers', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_16018', 'name': 'black beans', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup canned black beans'}, {'iid': 's_20041', 'name': 'brown rice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of cooked brown rice'}, {'iid': 's_11168', 'name': 'corn', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of cooked corn'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon cumin'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'lightly sauteed onions', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of chopped and lightly sauteed onions'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'peppers', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '3 large Red Peppers'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'salsa', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup of hot salsa (or add ¼ tsp cayenne if not hot)'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and Pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_1001009', 'name': 'cheddar', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 1/2 cup of shredded cheddar'}]}, {'rid': 's_639401', 'title': 'Cider-Braised Pork Shoulder With Caramelized Onion and Apple Confit', 'inst': 'Preheat oven to 400 F. Pat the pork dry and season with salt and pepper. Heat oil in a large ovenproof pot or Dutch oven with a lid. Brown pork on all sides, turning with tongs, 6-8 minutes per side. Transfer pork to a plate. Pour off excess fat from pot. Add onion and 1 teaspoon salt. Saut over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the onions are very soft and deep golden brown, 18-20 minutes. Add Calvados and stir to deglaze pan. Add apple, garlic and thyme and cook, stirring, 30 seconds. Return pork to pot, nestling it down in the onions. Add cider and chicken stock. Cover pot and place in oven. Reduce heat to 325 F. Braise until meat is very tender, 2 1/2 - 3 hours. Transfer pork to a cutting board and remove kitchen strings. Boil onion and apples until thickened and liquid slightly reduced, about 2 minutes. Stir in mustard. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cut pork into serving pieces and arrange on platter or individual serving plates. Spoon onion and apple confit over and around the meat.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/76WCQ5NG/cider-braised-pork-shoulder-with-caramelized-onion-and-apple-confit', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10072', 'name': 'tied pork shoulder', 'qty': 2.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 1/2 pounds tied pork shoulder'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10511282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '4 large yellow onions, halved, thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_10114037', 'name': 'calvados brandy', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup Calvados brandy'}, {'iid': 's_1089003', 'name': 'granny smith apple', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'inch', 'raw': '1 inch large Granny Smith apple, peeled, cored, cut ½" cubes'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 garlic cloves, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_2042', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon dried thyme or 1 tablespoon fresh thyme'}, {'iid': 's_1009016', 'name': 'apple cider', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup apple cider'}, {'iid': 's_6172', 'name': 'chicken stock', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup chicken stock'}, {'iid': 's_1032046', 'name': 'dijon mustard', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon Dijon mustard'}]}, {'rid': 's_665831', 'title': 'fennel, Peppers, Lettuce Salad', 'inst': 'Wash and chop up your veggies. Make a sald dressing of chopped up rosemary and olive oil. Pour over the salad.', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/VNXX86Q3/fennel-peppers-lettuce-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10111253', 'name': 'baby/lolo lettuce', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '3 cups of baby/lolo lettuce'}, {'iid': 's_11252', 'name': 'roquette lettuce', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '3 cups of roquette lettuce (arugula)'}, {'iid': 's_11957', 'name': 'fennel bulb and leaves', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of fennel bulb and leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11333', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 green pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 red pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11206', 'name': 'pickled cucumber', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '5 pickled cucumber'}, {'iid': 's_9195', 'name': 'blacks olives', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '10 blacks olives'}, {'iid': 's_2036', 'name': 'rosemary', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'sprigs', 'raw': '3 sprigs of rosemary'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon of olive oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_635701', 'title': 'Boudin', 'inst': 'Cook pork meat, liver and seasonings in water (to cover) until meat falls apart; remove meat and reserve some broth.Grind meat, onion, green onions and parsley (reserving about 1/2 cup each of green onion tops and parsley). Mix ground meat mixture with the 1/2 cups of green onion tops and parsley, rice and enough broth to make a moist dressing.Stuff dressing into casing, using a sausage stuffer.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/HN2YWSYN/boudin', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10220445', 'name': 'rice', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '6 cups cooked rice'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onions', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'bunches', 'raw': '2 bunches green onions, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch parsley, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_1065062', 'name': 'pork meat', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 pounds pork meat'}, {'iid': 's_10110', 'name': 'pork liver', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '1 1/2 pounds pork liver'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '5 teaspoons salt'}, {'iid': 's_1017063', 'name': 'sausage casings', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Sausage casings, soaked in cold water'}]}, {'rid': 's_982375', 'title': 'Instant Pot Pressure Cooker Pot Roast', 'inst': 'First, place the Instant Pot on the saute function. Once it is hot, add the olive oil and then add the roast. I like to sear all of the sides for a few minutes to help seal in the juices and to also give it that pretty coloring. Next, pour in the beef broth and seasoning sauce along with the chopped onion. Place the pressure cooker on manual and set for 30 minutes. After the first 30 minutes, do a quick release and then add the quartered potatoes and the carrots. Place on manual and then cook again for 15 minutes. Once finished do another quick release and carefully remove the roast to a serving dish. Take a large slotted spoon and remove the potatoes and carrots, and then save the flavored broth to serve over your dish.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/instant-pot-pressure-cooker-pot-roast-recipe/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'whole 30'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11960', 'name': 'baby carrots', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '12 small baby carrots'}, {'iid': 's_1006615', 'name': 'beed broth', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups beed broth'}, {'iid': 's_35177', 'name': 'roast', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '2-3 lb roast'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 Tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 onion (chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '4 medium potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_1042027', 'name': "dale's steal seasoning", 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': "¼ cup Dale's Steal Seasoning"}]}, {'rid': 's_1052360', 'title': 'The Secret to the Best Ever Instant Pot Lamb Stew', 'inst': "Wash, peel, cut, and prep the vegetables. Heat up the instant pot using the saut setting. Add in the oil, salt, pepper, and leeks. Cover with a standard kitchen lid and cook for about 3 minutes until they start to brown. Pour in the beer and honey. (The honey is optional but helps to soften and bring all of the flavors together.) Whisk together before setting in the meat and then layer the vegetables on top. Add the rest of the liquid and add any additional seasonings you'd prefer. Twist on the locking lid and cancel the saut mode. Select manual mode for 14 minutes. When the pressurized cook time has passed and the pot beeps, let the pot natural pressure release for 2 minutes before quick releasing the rest of the pressure. Stir the stew and then let cool for a few minutes prior to serving.", 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/best-instant-pot-lamb-stew/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_4581', 'name': 'avocado oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon olive or avocado oil'}, {'iid': 's_6170', 'name': 'beef stock', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '5 cups quality vegetable or beef stock'}, {'iid': 's_93619', 'name': 'guinness beer', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup guinness beer'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'honey optional', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon raw honey optional'}, {'iid': 's_17059', 'name': 'lamb stew meat', 'qty': 2.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2.5 pounds lamb stew meat'}, {'iid': 's_11246', 'name': 'leek', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large leek'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2-3 cups mini potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_11507', 'name': 'sweet potatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '2 medium sweet potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_2049', 'name': 'thyme and rosemary', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'fresh thyme and rosemary to taste'}]}, {'rid': 's_649946', 'title': 'Lentil, Sweet Potato and Spinach Soup', 'inst': 'Let the dry beans soak for a 2-3 hours before you start the soup. When ready to cook, pour the water in a pot, let boil and add the onions and garlic. Add the lentils, peanut butter, and bay leaves when the water comes to a steady boil. Cover the pot and cut up the potatoes and carrots. Let the lentils cook for an hour or so, checking on it periodically (adding water is common). Then add the potatoes and carrots, along with various seasonings (curry, salt, pepper and cumin) and cover. Make sure to taste as go and let cook for about another 45 minutes to an hour. Turn off the flame and place a bunch of fresh spinach on the bottom of a bowl, pour in the soup and enjoy!', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/3CY5B52M/lentil-sweet-potato-and-spinach-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaves', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '8 whole bay leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': 'bunch of carrots, cut up'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of cumin'}, {'iid': 's_2015', 'name': 'curry powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of curry powder'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic'}, {'iid': 's_10316069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups of dry lentils'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of sea salt'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': 'bunch of spinach'}, {'iid': 's_11507', 'name': 'sweet potato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 whole sweet potato, chopped up'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups water'}, {'iid': 's_10511282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 yellow onion, chopped up'}]}, {'rid': 's_632822', 'title': 'Asian Coleslaw with Baked Salmon', 'inst': 'Bake the Salmon1.Pre-heat your oven to 200C / 400F. Place aluminium foil in a roasting tray. Use enough foil so that you can wrap the fish in it loosely. Place the fish on the foil. Drizzle over the oil and the lemon juice. Sprinkle over the salt and the pepper.3.Cover your fish with the foil, making a loose parcel. Place the tray in the oven and allow to bake for 7 to 12 minutes. The cooking time will not only depend on your oven, but also on how thick the salmon filets are. You can bake the salmon in advance as it should be served at room temperature.To Make the Coleslaw and Dressing Mix the dressing ingredients, except for the chives, together in a bowl. I find the best way to do this is with a metal whisk. Then stir in the chives. Check for flavouring and adjust if you wish. Set aside. Place the salad ingredients in a large salad bowl.3.When you are ready to serve pour over the dressing and toss through until evenly mixed. Serve with the salmon on the top of your salad and the spoonful of wakame on top of the salmon and a few slices of avocado and a wedge of lime on the side.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TBR4BGWW/asian-coleslaw-with-baked-salmon', 'cui': 'asian', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'an avocado', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'An avocado, sliced and served on the side.'}, {'iid': 's_11043', 'name': 'oz. beansprouts', 'qty': 200.0, 'unit': 'gr', 'raw': '200gr / 7 oz. beansprouts'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'oz. carrot', 'qty': 200.0, 'unit': 'gr', 'raw': '200gr / 7 oz. grated carrot'}, {'iid': 's_11156', 'name': 'tbsp chives', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 x tbsp finely chopped chives'}, {'iid': 's_10111168', 'name': 'oz. corn', 'qty': 200.0, 'unit': 'gr', 'raw': '200gr / 7 oz. sweet corn'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Juice of 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'juice of lime', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Juice of 1 lime (About 2 x tbsps.)'}, {'iid': 's_93623', 'name': 'lettuce leaf', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'leaves', 'raw': '6 to 8 leaves of Chinese lettuce leaf, shredded'}, {'iid': 's_9159', 'name': 'limes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 x limes quartered.'}, {'iid': 's_1001116', 'name': 'tbsp mayonnaise', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 x tbsp good quality mayonnaise (or 2 x tbsp mayonnaise and 2 x tbsp natural yogurt – this will give a sharper result)'}, {'iid': 's_93830', 'name': 'tbsp japanese mirin', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 x tbsp Japanese Mirin'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 x tbsp of olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon filets of 150gr / 5 oz. each', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 x salmon filets of about 150gr / 5 oz. each'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_93695', 'name': 'cut julienne', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': '1 x courgette (zucchini), shredded or cut julienne'}, {'iid': 's_10011990', 'name': 'tsp wasabi paste', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 x tsp wasabi paste (more if you want more of a kick)'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'tbsp', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': 'tbsp per person of wakame (Japanese Seaweed Salad)'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'to finish', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'To Finish'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'to finish', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'To Finish'}]}, {'rid': 's_658753', 'title': 'Roma Tomato Bruschetta', 'inst': 'Slice the bread on a bias about 1/2 inch thick. We need about 10-12 slices.Take 2 tablespoons of extra virgin olive oil and add salt and pepper (about 1/3 teaspoon each - as per taste). Brush this on both sides of the bread. Place these slices on a sheet pan and bake for about 3-4 minutes in a 400 degree preheated oven till golden brown. Once one side is done, turn over the crostini to the other side to crisp that as well.When the crostini are hot out the oven, rub a garlic clove on them.Chop the tomatoes.Chiffonade the basil and add to the tomatoes. Add salt, pepper, olive oil and balsamic vinegar and let it rest for a few minutes.Put a generous amount of tomato on the crostini and serve.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/M3RH6LBH/roma-tomato-bruschetta', 'cui': 'mediterranean', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2069', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '4 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_18029', 'name': 'bread', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'loaf', 'raw': '1 loaf french bread'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'leaves', 'raw': '10 leaves fresh basil'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '4 mediums tomatoes, roma'}]}, {'rid': 's_662087', 'title': 'Stuffed Salmon With Tomato-Olive Tapenade', 'inst': 'Preheat oven to 350F.Pound salmon fillets and rub with olive oil and dill.In bowl, combine chopped spinach, onions, and garlic. Season with salt. Spread spinach mixture on salmon fillet. Slice brie and add on top. Carefully roll salmon and tie with string. Bake for about 15-18 minutes.Chop olives in food processor. Add chopped tomatoes and blend. Spread on top of salmon.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/CNBXP6TH/stuffed-salmon-with-tomato-olive-tapenade', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'primal', 'pescatarian', 'ketogenic'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1006', 'name': 'brie cheese', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Brie Cheese, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_2045', 'name': 'dill weed', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Dill weed, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '6 cloves of minced garlic'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Olive oil, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_9195', 'name': 'olives', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup olives'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 onion chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon filets', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 salmon filets'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup chopped spinach'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 large tomatoes'}]}, {'rid': 's_645032', 'title': 'Goldilocks Chia Seed Porridge', 'inst': "Lovingly mix all of the ingredient's together in your favorite cereal bowl, let sit for approx. 5 minutes or longer so that the Chia seeds can began to thicken into a gel-like consistency. You may prefer to add the Chia seeds and the hemp milk first to allow for the thickening process to take course before adding the remaining ingredient's, this shall be up to you.Once the cereal is thickened, think happy and enjoy!", 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/SHSG4TQK/goldilocks-chia-seed-porridge', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10012023', 'name': 'sesame seeds', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon Black Sesame seeds'}, {'iid': 's_98846', 'name': 'cacao nibs', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon Cacao nibs'}, {'iid': 's_12006', 'name': 'chia seeds', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons Chia seeds'}, {'iid': 's_98863', 'name': 'goji berries', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon Goji berries'}, {'iid': 's_98874', 'name': 'vanilla hemp milk', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup vanilla hemp milk'}, {'iid': 's_98994', 'name': 'lucuma powder', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 teaspoons Lucuma Powder'}, {'iid': 's_9176', 'name': 'mango', 'qty': 0.125, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/8 cup Fresh Mango, cubed'}, {'iid': 's_12014', 'name': 'pumpkin seeds', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon Pumpkin seeds'}, {'iid': 's_9316', 'name': 'strawberries', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 Fresh strawberries, sliced'}]}, {'rid': 's_645849', 'title': 'Grilled Salmon Salad With Blood Orange Cilantro Vinaigrette', 'inst': 'Place salmon steaks over aluminum foil on a heated grill. Brush with Blood Orange Cilantro Vinaigrette and sprinkle with salt and pepper.Grill for 6-9 minutes on each side.Wash mixed greens and place about a handful on each plate.Wash and half grape tomatoes and sprinkle over greens.Slice cucumber and lay over the greens.Peel and julienne jicama and place over the greens.Arrange each slice of salmon over the greens and slice.Spoon the Avocado Corn Salsa over the salmon, and drizzle Blood Orange Cilantro Vinaigrette over the salad.Avocado Corn Salsa and Blood Orange Cilantro Vinaigrette are listed as separate recipes in my recipe file.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/N5WHVQHC/grilled-salmon-salad-with-blood-orange-cilantro-vinaigrette', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'fodmap friendly', 'whole 30', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1009200', 'name': 'blood orange cilantro vinaigrette', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Blood Orange Cilantro Vinaigrette'}, {'iid': 's_11206', 'name': 'cucumber', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Cucumber'}, {'iid': 's_10111529', 'name': 'grape tomatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Grape Tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_11603', 'name': 'jicama', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Jicama*'}, {'iid': 's_21052', 'name': 'greens', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Mixed greens'}, {'iid': 's_10015076', 'name': 'salmon steaks', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 salmon steaks, 1" thick'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper to taste'}]}, {'rid': 's_641893', 'title': 'Easy Cheesy Pizza Casserole', 'inst': "Brown ground beef in skillet; drain fat. Mix in pasta or pizza sauce and pepper flakes; set aside. Mix ricotta cheese with the herbs and Parmesan in a separate bowl; set aside. Mix the dry ingredients for the biscuits. Add milk and stir until combined. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.  Spray a 13 x 9 pan with non-stick spray.  Drop biscuit dough by teaspoons in the bottom of pan, spacing evenly.  It's OK if there is space between the dough--it will expand as it's cooked.  Top with ground beef mixture and dot with the ricotta cheese mixture. Bake at 375 for about 20 min or until biscuits are puffed and beginning to get golden brown. Top with mozzarella and provolone cheeses and distribute pepperoni slices evenly over top, increase oven temperature to 425 degrees.  Return to oven and bake until cheeses are melted and beginning to bubble.  This should take about 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before slicing and serving.  May be topped with the additional Parmesan cheese.", 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZTHZWCWF/easy-cheesy-pizza-casserole', 'cui': 'mediterranean', 'diets': [], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10023572', 'name': 'equivalent amount of a ground beef/bulk sausage mix', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '1 lb ground beef or equivalent amount of a ground beef/bulk Italian sausage mix'}, {'iid': 's_1036', 'name': 'ricotta', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup ricotta'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'oregano', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of oregano'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of basil'}, {'iid': 's_1032', 'name': 'parmesan cheese', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'iid': 's_10011549', 'name': 'pasta sauce', 'qty': 26.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 - 26 oz jar of pasta sauce'}, {'iid': 's_11549', 'name': 'pizza sauce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'can', 'raw': '1 can pizza sauce'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'pepper flakes', 'qty': 0.125, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/8 - 1/2 tsp crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'iid': 's_1007057', 'name': 'pepperoni', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Pepperoni slices (I used 1/2 of a package of Hormel brand)'}, {'iid': 's_1001026', 'name': 'mozzarella', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups shredded mozzarella'}, {'iid': 's_1035', 'name': 'aged provolone', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup shredded aged Provolone'}, {'iid': 's_1033', 'name': 'herbed parmesan drop biscuits', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Herbed Parmesan Drop Biscuits'}, {'iid': 's_1033', 'name': 'additional parmesan cheese', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Additional Parmesan cheese for topping'}, {'iid': 's_18010', 'name': 'baking mix', 'qty': 2.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '2 1/4 cup baking mix (like Bisquick or Jiffy)'}, {'iid': 's_1032', 'name': 'parmesan cheese', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'iid': 's_1022027', 'name': 'seasoning', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp Italian seasoning'}, {'iid': 's_1077', 'name': 'milk', 'qty': 0.6666667, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '2/3 cup milk'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'or', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'serving', 'raw': '-or-'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'or', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': '-or-'}]}, {'rid': 's_638780', 'title': 'Chock Full Of Broccoli Soup', 'inst': 'Separate broccoli florets from stems. Cut florets into bite-sized pieces; trim and peel stems, and cut into bite-sized pieces. Place soup pot over medium heat and add oil; when hot, add onions and broccoli stems, and stir well to coat with oil. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes, or until onions are translucent and tender. Uncover, add garlic, blend well, and cook 1 minute longer. Add florets and chicken broth; bring to boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes, or until broccoli is tender. Remove from heat and whisk in miso; allow to cool 5 minutes.Puree half the soup in several batches in blender, adding some tofu with each batch.  Return pureed soup to the pot; stir well to blend. Thin with additional chicken broth, if desired. Add salt, pepper, and tarragon, if using. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/MYJMGP67/chock-full-of-broccoli-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'to 3 broccoli', 'qty': 2.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 1/2 pounds to 3 broccoli (2 bunches)'}, {'iid': 's_6970', 'name': 'to 5 chicken broth', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups to 5 low-sodium chicken broth'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons minced garlic'}, {'iid': 's_16112', 'name': 'mellow miso', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons sweet or mellow white miso'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups chopped onion'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_16161', 'name': 'lite silken tofu', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '3/4 cup lite silken tofu (about ½ pound), preferably Nasoya'}, {'iid': 's_2041', 'name': 'to 2 tarragon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon to 2 chopped fresh tarragon, optional'}]}, {'rid': 's_664501', 'title': 'Vegan Taco bowls with Cilantro Lime Cauliflower Rice', 'inst': 'Set the nuts to soak in a bowl of water 2-8 hours before preparing the meat.Preheat the oven to 375 F and line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.Finely chop the cauliflower into rice-sized pieces, or pulse in the food processor until the desired consistency. Toss with the oil and spread onto the baking sheet in an even layer. Bake for 18 minutes, stirring halfway through.While the cauliflower rice is cooking, prepare the guacamole and taco meat. Cut the avocado into large chunks and place into a small bowl. Add the lime juice and mash the avocado to a chunky puree or your preferred consistency. Stir in the cilantro, jalapeno, onion and spices. Set aside. Remove the nuts from the water and place into a small food processor. Discard the water. Pulse the nuts until theyve reached a ground meat consistency, I find about 5-7 pulses works. Transfer to a bowl and stir in the salt, cumin, garlic powder, and red chili powder. Set aside.When the cauliflower is done, transfer to a mixing bowl while still warm and stir in the lime, cilantro, and salt.To assemble the bowls, layer 1 cup of the cauliflower rice in a bowl with taco nut meat, a dollop of guacamole, fresh tomatoes, and a sprinkling of fresh cilantro. Serve immediately with an additional slice of lime if desired.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/DKDKL4GJ/vegan-taco-bowls-with-cilantro-lime-cauliflower-rice', 'cui': 'mexican', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'avocado oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp avocado oil or other extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'cauliflower', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'large head', 'raw': '½ large head cauliflower (you need 4 cups finely chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_2009', 'name': 'new mexico chili powder', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '¾ tsp New Mexico red chili powder'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'fresh cilantro, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1022020', 'name': 'garlic powder', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '¼ tsp garlic powder'}, {'iid': 's_1039037', 'name': 'hass avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Hass avocado'}, {'iid': 's_11979', 'name': 'jalapeno', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp fresh jalapeno, seeded and finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'lime juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp fresh lime juice'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 onion'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 tomato'}, {'iid': 's_12155', 'name': 'walnuts', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups Walnuts (chopped)'}]}, {'rid': 's_664785', 'title': 'Venison Sliders', 'inst': 'Sprinkle roast evenly with salt and pepper. Place in a crock pot and add liquid. Cook on low 5 to 6 hours. Remove roast from crockpot and let sit for at least 10 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat your sandwich press, grill pan or skillet and saute your onions (you can choose to leave the onions raw if you prefer).Thinly slice the roast.Slice bread in small sandwich sized portions and spread on your condiment of choice. Pile on spinach, onion, venison and cheese in which ever order strikes your fancy. Place in your sandwich press and make sure to press and hold the lid down for at least 30 seconds. Let cook for 5 minutes until cheese is melted and bread is toasted. Serve and enjoy!', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/BL8YDZTV/venison-sliders', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11457', 'name': 'baby spinach', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Baby spinach'}, {'iid': 's_18064', 'name': 'bread', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'loaf', 'raw': '1 loaf of hearty bread'}, {'iid': 's_35177', 'name': 'veni-son round roast', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '3 pounds veni\xadson round roast'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large onion'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'teas pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 teas pepper'}, {'iid': 's_27048', 'name': 'steak sauce', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Chipolte mayo, mayo, or steak sauce'}, {'iid': 's_14355', 'name': 'tea salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 tea salt'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'liq\xaduid', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup liq\xaduid (I used a steak\xadhouse mari\xadnade.)'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'liq-uid', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup liq\xaduid (I used a steak\xadhouse mari\xadnade.)'}]}, {'rid': 's_1095750', 'title': 'Whole Wheat Spaghetti with Basil Avocado Pesto', 'inst': 'Place the fresh basil, avocado, garlic, cashews, and sea salt into a food processor and blitz until everything is smooth, scraping down the sides occasionally.While the food processor is running, add in the water 1 tbsp at a time until you have a creamy pesto.Cook whole wheat spaghetti according to package instructions. Drain the pasta, toss with pesto, serve with a little extra fresh basil and Parmesan.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/GYVS8LP3/oil-free-pesto-w-basil-avocado', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup Fresh Basil (packed)'}, {'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 Ripe Avocado'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic'}, {'iid': 's_12087', 'name': 'cashew nuts', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup Cashew Nuts'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '3 tbsp Water'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4 tsp Sea Salt'}, {'iid': 's_10020124', 'name': 'spaghetti', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '8 oz whole wheat spaghetti'}]}, {'rid': 's_658414', 'title': 'Roast Cauliflower Salad with Green Beans and Cherry Tomatoes', 'inst': 'Pre-heat your oven to 220C / 420F Place the cauliflower florets in a roasting tin. Drizzle over 1 tablespoon olive oil and the lemon juice. Sprinkle over the salt and garlic, mix through and roast in the oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until the cauliflower has softened slightly and taken on some colour.Whilst the cauliflower is cooking place the salad ingredients in a bowl. Add your beans whilst they are hot.  The heat helps bring out and blend the rest of the flavours. Add the cauliflower to your dish (also hot if you like). Add the dressing ingredients to your salad and mix through until everything is covered, check for seasoning, sprinkle with the almonds and serve.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZCRN8JDC/roast-cauliflower-salad-with-green-beans-and-cherry-tomatoes', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_12061', 'name': 'almonds', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1.5 oz. toasted flaked almonds'}, {'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'cauliflower', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium cauliflower'}, {'iid': 's_10311529', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes', 'qty': 14.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '14 oz. cherry tomatoes, halved or quartered.'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat leaved parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': 'A handful of flat leaved parsley chopped finely'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 garlic cloves chopped finely'}, {'iid': 's_11052', 'name': 'green beans', 'qty': 1.1, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '1.1 lb green beans'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice of 1/2 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '3 tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'spring onions', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 spring onions (scallions) chopped finely'}]}, {'rid': 's_716300', 'title': 'Plantain Pizza', 'inst': 'Dissolve the yeast in warm water and leave to stand for about 5 minutes. Mix the oil, flour, salt, sugar and mashed plantain and pour in the dissolved yeast.Knead the dough till its elastic which may take aBout 15-20 minutes By hand or 10 minutes in a mixer.Coat a Bowl lightly with oil and place the dough in it. Cover with a plastic wrap and leave to rise between 1.5 – 2 hours.While the dough is rising, heat up the oil for the sauce, fry the Blended tomato and pepper, season and stir fry the Beef in the tomato sauce. Set aside.When the dough rises, divide into two. Sprinkle some flour on a flat surface and with a rolling pin, flatten out the dough but not excessively. Cut the dough into your desired shape, rub some oil on it and spread your sauce and toppings on it and set aside. Heat up your oven to 350 F and place your pizza dough on a lightly oiled foil pan and Bake for 12-15 mins. Serve warm', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://www.afrolems.com/2014/03/08/plantain-pizza/', 'cui': 'mediterranean', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_23572', 'name': 'beef', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of chopped Beef'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Bell pepper (Blended)'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell peppers', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': '1 handful of chopped bell peppers'}, {'iid': 's_10120129', 'name': 'bread flour', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups of Bread flour'}, {'iid': 's_10014412', 'name': 'seasoning cube', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Seasoning cube'}, {'iid': 's_4582', 'name': 'oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon of oil'}, {'iid': 's_4582', 'name': 'oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': 'A handful of chopped onions'}, {'iid': 's_10099295', 'name': 'over-ripe plantain', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 over-ripe plantain (Mashed)'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_19335', 'name': 'sugar', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon of sugar'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomato)', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 tomato(Blended)'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup of water'}, {'iid': 's_18375', 'name': 'yeast', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '1.5 teaspoons of yeast'}]}, {'rid': 's_646034', 'title': 'Guinness Braised Corned Beef and Cabbage', 'inst': "Season both sides of the corned beef liberally with pepper. The corning of the beef makes the beef salty enough, so no need to add more. Heat 1 TBSP oil in a large, shallow oven-safe pot over medium-high heat. Add beef and sear each side for about 3 minutes, just to develop a nice brown crust. This will seal in the beef's juices. Remove beef to a plate. Pour guinness into the pot to deglaze. Scrape up any browned bits. Add beef broth, pickling spice, brown sugar, bay leaf, and minced garlic. Bring mixture up to a simmer. Return the beef to the pot with any additional juices that have accumulated on the plate. Cover the pot and place on the bottom rack in your oven. Bake for 2 1/2 - 3 hours, or until a fork can easily be inserted into the meat. Baste the meat with the surrounding juices every 30 minutes or so. After 2 hours, add carrots, parsnips, and potatoes to the pot. They will only take about 25-30 minutes of simmering to cook. Remove pot from the oven. Place beef on a cutting board and let it rest for 15 minutes before carving into thin slices (cut against the grain of the meat). Remove vegetables and arrange them on a serving platter. Cover with foil. Place the pot on the burner and bring sauce to a boil. Add cabbage and cook for about 7 minutes, until it has softened. Place the cabbage on the serving platter with the other vegetables. Strain the sauce in the pot and stir in 2 or 3 TBSP of spicy honey mustard until dissolved. Place in a small dish or gravy boat with a ladle and serve alongside the beef. After slicing the beef and arranging it on the serving platter, ladle the guinness mustard sauce over the top to rehydrate and glaze the beef and vegetables.", 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/5NNYR6RD/guinness-braised-corned-beef-and-cabbage', 'cui': 'european', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10013346', 'name': 'corned beef brisket', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 pounds corned beef brisket'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound carrots, roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11298', 'name': 'parsnips', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound parsnips, roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potatoes', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '3 large potatoes, peeled and quartered'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_93619', 'name': 'guinness', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups Guinness'}, {'iid': 's_6008', 'name': 'beef broth', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups beef broth'}, {'iid': 's_1032027', 'name': 'pickling spice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons pickling spice'}, {'iid': 's_19334', 'name': 'brown sugar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon brown sugar'}, {'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaf', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 bay leaf'}, {'iid': 's_99227', 'name': 'spicy honey mustard', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 spicy honey mustard'}]}, {'rid': 's_640275', 'title': 'Crab Cakes Eggs Benedict', 'inst': 'Prepare the crab cakes:Cook onion and celery in 4 tablespoons butter over moderately low heat, until tender and transfer to a bowl. Stir in crab and bread crumbs.In a small bowl whisk together mayonnaise, seafood seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, parsley, and salt and pepper to taste and stir into crab mixture until combined well.Line a baking sheet with wax paper. Form crab mixture into 6 flattened rounds. Chill crab cakes, covered with plastic wrap, at least 1 hour. Heat 1 tablespoon butter over moderate heat until foam subsides and cook half of crab cakes until golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Cook remaining cakes in remaining tablespoon butter in same manner.Prepare Knorr Hollandaise Sauce according to package instructions.Poach the eggs:Fill a medium sized sauce pan half way with water. Add 1/2 teaspoon of white vinegar (this is optional but the vinegar helps hold the egg together). Bring to a gentle boil and carefully add eggs (1-2 at a time works best). Poach eggs for 2-3 minutes or until yolk has set to your preference. Layer ingredients as follows: English muffin, crab cakes (1 each muffin), eggs, Hollandaise sauce.', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/P53KDVS3/crab-cakes-eggs-benedict', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11143', 'name': 'celery', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup finely chopped celery'}, {'iid': 's_18079', 'name': 'bread crumbs', 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/3 cup fine dry bread crumbs'}, {'iid': 's_1123', 'name': 'eggs', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 Eggs'}, {'iid': 's_18439', 'name': 'muffins', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 English Muffins'}, {'iid': 's_93802', 'name': 'knorr hollandaise sauce mix', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'package', 'raw': '1 package Knorr Hollandaise Sauce Mix'}, {'iid': 's_6168', 'name': 'hot sauce', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'drops', 'raw': '3 drops hot sauce'}, {'iid': 's_10115136', 'name': 'lump crab meat', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound lump crab meat'}, {'iid': 's_4025', 'name': 'mayonnaise', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup mayonnaise'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup finely chopped onion'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons minced parsley'}, {'iid': 's_1032034', 'name': 'seafood seasoning', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon seafood seasoning'}, {'iid': 's_1145', 'name': 'butter', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '6 tablespoons unsalted butter'}, {'iid': 's_6971', 'name': 'worcestershire sauce', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce'}]}, {'rid': 's_649405', 'title': 'Lebanese Lentil Soup', 'inst': 'Heat lentils, ham bone, and water in large saucepan to boiling. Reduce heat. Skim the excess; skim off the top as it forms. Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes. Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat until hot. Add spinach, onion, garlic, and coriander seed; saute until the spinach is wilted. Add rice and the spinach mixture to lentils. Simmer, uncovered, until lentils and onions are tender, 15-20 minutes. Remove ham bone, pull ham from bone, chop the meat and stir into the soup. Add more water, if needed, to thin the soup. Stir in the lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste. Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/XSWN5NTY/lebanese-lentil-soup', 'cui': 'middle eastern', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10220445', 'name': 'rice', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup cooked rice'}, {'iid': 's_2013', 'name': 'coriander seed', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon coriander seed, crushed'}, {'iid': 's_10416069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups dried lentils'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '8 cloves of garlic'}, {'iid': 's_12011111', 'name': 'ham bone', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 ham bone with some meat left on it'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup fresh lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Onion, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups trimmed spinach cut in ½-inch strips (about 8 oz.)'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '8 cups water (can use 4 c. water and 4 c. 3 tablespoons olive oil'}]}], 'next_offset': 200}
